21/* This file implements mangling of C++ names according to the IA64
22 C++ ABI specification. A mangled name encodes a function or
23 variable's name, scope, type, and/or template arguments into a text
24 identifier. This identifier is used as the function's or
25 variable's linkage name, to preserve compatibility between C++'s
26 language features (templates, scoping, and overloading) and C
27 linkers.
28
29 Additionally, g++ uses mangled names internally. To support this,
30 mangling of types is allowed, even though the mangled name of a
31 type should not appear by itself as an exported name. Ditto for
32 uninstantiated templates.
33
34 The primary entry point for this module is mangle_decl, which
35 returns an identifier containing the mangled name for a decl.
36 Additional entry points are provided to build mangled names of
37 particular constructs when the appropriate decl for that construct
38 is not available. These are:
39
40 mangle_typeinfo_for_type: typeinfo data
41 mangle_typeinfo_string_for_type: typeinfo type name
42 mangle_vtbl_for_type: virtual table data
43 mangle_vtt_for_type: VTT data
44 mangle_ctor_vtbl_for_type: `C-in-B' constructor virtual table data
45 mangle_thunk: thunk function or entry */
46

78/* Nonzero if NODE is a class template-id. We can't rely on
79 CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE here because of tricky bugs in the parser
80 that hard to distinguish A<T> from A, where A<T> is the type as
81 instantiated outside of the template, and A is the type used
82 without parameters inside the template. */
83#define CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_ID_P(NODE) \
84 (TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (NODE) != NULL \
85 && (TREE_CODE (NODE) == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM \
86 || (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (NODE) != NULL \
87 && (PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (CLASSTYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (NODE))))))
88
89/* For deciding whether to set G.need_abi_warning, we need to consider both
90 warn_abi_version and flag_abi_compat_version. */
91#define abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses(N) \
92 (abi_version_crosses (N) || abi_compat_version_crosses (N))
93
94/* And sometimes we can simplify the code path if we don't need to worry about
95 previous ABIs. */
96#define abi_flag_at_least(flag,N) (flag == 0 || flag >= N)
97#define any_abi_below(N) \
98 (!abi_version_at_least (N) \
99 || !abi_flag_at_least (warn_abi_version, (N)) \
100 || !abi_flag_at_least (flag_abi_compat_version, (N)))

102/* Things we only need one of. This module is not reentrant. */
103struct GTY(()) globals {
104 /* An array of the current substitution candidates, in the order
105 we've seen them. */
106 vec<tree, va_gc> *substitutions;
107
108 /* The entity that is being mangled. */
109 tree GTY ((skip)) entity;
110
111 /* How many parameter scopes we are inside. */
112 int parm_depth;
113
114 /* True if the mangling will be different in a future version of the
115 ABI. */
116 bool need_abi_warning;
117
118 /* True if the mangling will be different in C++17 mode. */
119 bool need_cxx1z_warning;
120};

245/* Append a single character to the end of the mangled
246 representation. */
247#define write_char(CHAR) \
248 obstack_1grow (mangle_obstack, (CHAR))
249
250/* Append a sized buffer to the end of the mangled representation. */
251#define write_chars(CHAR, LEN) \
252 obstack_grow (mangle_obstack, (CHAR), (LEN))
253
254/* Append a NUL-terminated string to the end of the mangled
255 representation. */
256#define write_string(STRING) \
257 obstack_grow (mangle_obstack, (STRING), strlen (STRING))
258
259/* Nonzero if NODE1 and NODE2 are both TREE_LIST nodes and have the
260 same purpose (context, which may be a type) and value (template
261 decl). See write_template_prefix for more information on what this
262 is used for. */
263#define NESTED_TEMPLATE_MATCH(NODE1, NODE2) \
264 (TREE_CODE (NODE1) == TREE_LIST \
265 && TREE_CODE (NODE2) == TREE_LIST \
266 && ((TYPE_P (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE1)) \
267 && same_type_p (TREE_PURPOSE (NODE1), TREE_PURPOSE (NODE2))) \
268 || TREE_PURPOSE (NODE1) == TREE_PURPOSE (NODE2)) \
269 && TREE_VALUE (NODE1) == TREE_VALUE (NODE2))
270
271/* Write out an unsigned quantity in base 10. */
272#define write_unsigned_number(NUMBER) \
273 write_number ((NUMBER), /*unsigned_p=*/1, 10)

275/* If DECL is a template instance (including the uninstantiated template
276 itself), return nonzero and, if TEMPLATE_INFO is non-NULL, set
277 *TEMPLATE_INFO to its template info. Otherwise return zero. */
278
279static int
280decl_is_template_id (const tree decl, tree* const template_info)
281{
282 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
283 {
284 /* TYPE_DECLs are handled specially. Look at its type to decide
285 if this is a template instantiation. */
286 const tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
287
288 if (CLASS_TYPE_P (type) && CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_ID_P (type))
289 {
290 if (template_info != NULL)
291 /* For a templated TYPE_DECL, the template info is hanging
292 off the type. */
293 *template_info = TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (type);
294 return 1;
295 }
296 }
297 else
298 {
299 /* Check if this is a primary template. */
300 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) != NULL
301 && VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl)
302 && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
303 && PRIMARY_TEMPLATE_P (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (decl))
304 && TREE_CODE (decl) != TEMPLATE_DECL)
305 {
306 if (template_info != NULL)
307 /* For most templated decls, the template info is hanging
308 off the decl. */
309 *template_info = DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl);
310 return 1;
311 }
312 }
313
314 /* It's not a template id. */
315 return 0;
316}

318/* Produce debugging output of current substitution candidates. */
319
320static void
321dump_substitution_candidates (void)
322{
323 unsigned i;
324 tree el;
325
326 fprintf (stderr, " ++ substitutions ");
327 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (*G.substitutions, i, el)
328 {
329 const char *name = "???";
330
331 if (i > 0)
332 fprintf (stderr, " ");
333 if (DECL_P (el))
334 name = IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (el));
335 else if (TREE_CODE (el) == TREE_LIST)
336 name = IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (TREE_VALUE (el)));
337 else if (TYPE_NAME (el))
338 name = TYPE_NAME_STRING (el);
339 fprintf (stderr, " S%d_ = ", i - 1);
340 if (TYPE_P (el) &&
341 (CP_TYPE_RESTRICT_P (el)
342 || CP_TYPE_VOLATILE_P (el)
343 || CP_TYPE_CONST_P (el)))
344 fprintf (stderr, "CV-");
345 fprintf (stderr, "%s (%s at %p)\n",
346 name, get_tree_code_name (TREE_CODE (el)), (void *) el);
347 }
348}

350/* <exception-spec> ::=
351 Do -- non-throwing exception specification
352 DO <expression> E -- computed (instantiation-dependent) noexcept
353 Dw <type>* E -- throw (types) */
354
355static void
356write_exception_spec (tree spec)
357{
358
359 if (!spec || spec == noexcept_false_spec)
360 /* Nothing. */
361 return;
362
363 if (!flag_noexcept_type)
364 {
365 G.need_cxx1z_warning = true;
366 return;
367 }
368
369 if (spec == noexcept_true_spec || spec == empty_except_spec)
370 write_string ("Do");
371 else if (tree expr = TREE_PURPOSE (spec))
372 {
373 /* noexcept (expr) */
374 gcc_assert (uses_template_parms (expr));
375 write_string ("DO");
376 write_expression (expr);
377 write_char ('E');
378 }
379 else
380 {
381 /* throw (type-list) */
382 write_string ("Dw");
383 for (tree t = spec; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
384 write_type (TREE_VALUE (t));
385 write_char ('E');
386 }
387}

389/* Both decls and types can be substitution candidates, but sometimes
390 they refer to the same thing. For instance, a TYPE_DECL and
391 RECORD_TYPE for the same class refer to the same thing, and should
392 be treated accordingly in substitutions. This function returns a
393 canonicalized tree node representing NODE that is used when adding
394 and substitution candidates and finding matches. */
395
396static inline tree
397canonicalize_for_substitution (tree node)
398{
399 /* For a TYPE_DECL, use the type instead. */
400 if (TREE_CODE (node) == TYPE_DECL)
401 node = TREE_TYPE (node);
402 if (TYPE_P (node)
403 && TYPE_CANONICAL (node) != node
404 && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (node) != node)
405 {
406 tree orig = node;
407 /* Here we want to strip the topmost typedef only.
408 We need to do that so is_std_substitution can do proper
409 name matching. */
410 if (TREE_CODE (node) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
411 /* Use build_qualified_type and TYPE_QUALS here to preserve
412 the old buggy mangling of attribute noreturn with abi<5. */
413 node = build_qualified_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (node),
414 TYPE_QUALS (node));
415 else
416 node = cp_build_qualified_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (node),
417 cp_type_quals (node));
418 if (TREE_CODE (node) == FUNCTION_TYPE
419 || TREE_CODE (node) == METHOD_TYPE)
420 {
421 node = build_ref_qualified_type (node, type_memfn_rqual (orig));
422 tree r = canonical_eh_spec (TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (orig));
423 if (flag_noexcept_type)
424 node = build_exception_variant (node, r);
425 else
426 /* Set the warning flag if appropriate. */
427 write_exception_spec (r);
428 }
429 }
430 return node;
431}
432
433/* Add NODE as a substitution candidate. NODE must not already be on
434 the list of candidates. */
435
436static void
437add_substitution (tree node)
438{
439 tree c;
440
441 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
442 fprintf (stderr, " ++ add_substitution (%s at %10p)\n",
443 get_tree_code_name (TREE_CODE (node)), (void *) node);
444
445 /* Get the canonicalized substitution candidate for NODE. */
446 c = canonicalize_for_substitution (node);
447 if (DEBUG_MANGLE && c != node)
448 fprintf (stderr, " ++ using candidate (%s at %10p)\n",
449 get_tree_code_name (TREE_CODE (node)), (void *) node);
450 node = c;
451
452 /* Make sure NODE isn't already a candidate. */
453 if (flag_checking)
454 {
455 int i;
456 tree candidate;
457
458 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (G.substitutions, i, candidate)
459 {
460 gcc_assert (!(DECL_P (node) && node == candidate));
461 gcc_assert (!(TYPE_P (node) && TYPE_P (candidate)
462 && same_type_p (node, candidate)));
463 }
464 }
465
466 /* Put the decl onto the varray of substitution candidates. */
467 vec_safe_push (G.substitutions, node);
468
469 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
470 dump_substitution_candidates ();
471}

473/* Helper function for find_substitution. Returns nonzero if NODE,
474 which may be a decl or a CLASS_TYPE, is a template-id with template
475 name of substitution_index[INDEX] in the ::std namespace. */
476
477static inline int
478is_std_substitution (const tree node,
479 const substitution_identifier_index_t index)
480{
481 tree type = NULL;
482 tree decl = NULL;
483
484 if (DECL_P (node))
485 {
486 type = TREE_TYPE (node);
487 decl = node;
488 }
489 else if (CLASS_TYPE_P (node))
490 {
491 type = node;
492 decl = TYPE_NAME (node);
493 }
494 else
495 /* These are not the droids you're looking for. */
496 return 0;
497
498 return (DECL_NAMESPACE_STD_P (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (decl))
499 && TYPE_LANG_SPECIFIC (type)
500 && TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (type)
501 && (DECL_NAME (TYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (type))
502 == subst_identifiers[index]));
503}
504
505/* Return the ABI tags (the TREE_VALUE of the "abi_tag" attribute entry) for T,
506 which can be a decl or type. */
507
508static tree
509get_abi_tags (tree t)
510{
511 if (!t || TREE_CODE (t) == NAMESPACE_DECL)
512 return NULL_TREE;
513
514 if (DECL_P (t) && DECL_DECLARES_TYPE_P (t))
515 t = TREE_TYPE (t);
516
517 tree attrs;
518 if (TYPE_P (t))
519 attrs = TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (t);
520 else
521 attrs = DECL_ATTRIBUTES (t);
522
523 tree tags = lookup_attribute ("abi_tag", attrs);
524 if (tags)
525 tags = TREE_VALUE (tags);
526 return tags;
527}
528
529/* Helper function for find_substitution. Returns nonzero if NODE,
530 which may be a decl or a CLASS_TYPE, is the template-id
531 ::std::identifier<char>, where identifier is
532 substitution_index[INDEX]. */
533
534static inline int
535is_std_substitution_char (const tree node,
536 const substitution_identifier_index_t index)
537{
538 tree args;
539 /* Check NODE's name is ::std::identifier. */
540 if (!is_std_substitution (node, index))
541 return 0;
542 /* Figure out its template args. */
543 if (DECL_P (node))
544 args = DECL_TI_ARGS (node);
545 else if (CLASS_TYPE_P (node))
546 args = CLASSTYPE_TI_ARGS (node);
547 else
548 /* Oops, not a template. */
549 return 0;
550 /* NODE's template arg list should be <char>. */
551 return
552 TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args) == 1
553 && TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0) == char_type_node;
554}
555
556/* Check whether a substitution should be used to represent NODE in
557 the mangling.
558
559 First, check standard special-case substitutions.
560
561 <substitution> ::= St
562 # ::std
563
564 ::= Sa
565 # ::std::allocator
566
567 ::= Sb
568 # ::std::basic_string
569
570 ::= Ss
571 # ::std::basic_string<char,
572 ::std::char_traits<char>,
573 ::std::allocator<char> >
574
575 ::= Si
576 # ::std::basic_istream<char, ::std::char_traits<char> >
577
578 ::= So
579 # ::std::basic_ostream<char, ::std::char_traits<char> >
580
581 ::= Sd
582 # ::std::basic_iostream<char, ::std::char_traits<char> >
583
584 Then examine the stack of currently available substitution
585 candidates for entities appearing earlier in the same mangling
586
587 If a substitution is found, write its mangled representation and
588 return nonzero. If none is found, just return zero. */
589
590static int
591find_substitution (tree node)
592{
593 int i;
594 const int size = vec_safe_length (G.substitutions);
595 tree decl;
596 tree type;
597 const char *abbr = NULL;
598
599 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
600 fprintf (stderr, " ++ find_substitution (%s at %p)\n",
601 get_tree_code_name (TREE_CODE (node)), (void *) node);
602
603 /* Obtain the canonicalized substitution representation for NODE.
604 This is what we'll compare against. */
605 node = canonicalize_for_substitution (node);
606
607 /* Check for builtin substitutions. */
608
609 decl = TYPE_P (node) ? TYPE_NAME (node) : node;
610 type = TYPE_P (node) ? node : TREE_TYPE (node);
611
612 /* Check for std::allocator. */
613 if (decl
614 && is_std_substitution (decl, SUBID_ALLOCATOR)
615 && !CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
616 abbr = "Sa";
617
618 /* Check for std::basic_string. */
619 else if (decl && is_std_substitution (decl, SUBID_BASIC_STRING))
620 {
621 if (TYPE_P (node))
622 {
623 /* If this is a type (i.e. a fully-qualified template-id),
624 check for
625 std::basic_string <char,
626 std::char_traits<char>,
627 std::allocator<char> > . */
628 if (cp_type_quals (type) == TYPE_UNQUALIFIED
629 && CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE (type))
630 {
631 tree args = CLASSTYPE_TI_ARGS (type);
632 if (TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args) == 3
633 && same_type_p (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0), char_type_node)
634 && is_std_substitution_char (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 1),
635 SUBID_CHAR_TRAITS)
636 && is_std_substitution_char (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 2),
637 SUBID_ALLOCATOR))
638 abbr = "Ss";
639 }
640 }
641 else
642 /* Substitute for the template name only if this isn't a type. */
643 abbr = "Sb";
644 }
645
646 /* Check for basic_{i,o,io}stream. */
647 else if (TYPE_P (node)
648 && cp_type_quals (type) == TYPE_UNQUALIFIED
649 && CLASS_TYPE_P (type)
650 && CLASSTYPE_USE_TEMPLATE (type)
651 && CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (type) != NULL)
652 {
653 /* First, check for the template
654 args <char, std::char_traits<char> > . */
655 tree args = CLASSTYPE_TI_ARGS (type);
656 if (TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args) == 2
657 && TYPE_P (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0))
658 && same_type_p (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0), char_type_node)
659 && is_std_substitution_char (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 1),
660 SUBID_CHAR_TRAITS))
661 {
662 /* Got them. Is this basic_istream? */
663 if (is_std_substitution (decl, SUBID_BASIC_ISTREAM))
664 abbr = "Si";
665 /* Or basic_ostream? */
666 else if (is_std_substitution (decl, SUBID_BASIC_OSTREAM))
667 abbr = "So";
668 /* Or basic_iostream? */
669 else if (is_std_substitution (decl, SUBID_BASIC_IOSTREAM))
670 abbr = "Sd";
671 }
672 }
673
674 /* Check for namespace std. */
675 else if (decl && DECL_NAMESPACE_STD_P (decl))
676 {
677 write_string ("St");
678 return 1;
679 }
680
681 tree tags = NULL_TREE;
682 if (OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (node) || DECL_CLASS_TEMPLATE_P (node))
683 tags = get_abi_tags (type);
684 /* Now check the list of available substitutions for this mangling
685 operation. */
686 if (!abbr || tags) for (i = 0; i < size; ++i)
687 {
688 tree candidate = (*G.substitutions)[i];
689 /* NODE is a matched to a candidate if it's the same decl node or
690 if it's the same type. */
691 if (decl == candidate
692 || (TYPE_P (candidate) && type && TYPE_P (node)
693 && same_type_p (type, candidate))
694 || NESTED_TEMPLATE_MATCH (node, candidate))
695 {
696 write_substitution (i);
697 return 1;
698 }
699 }
700
701 if (!abbr)
702 /* No substitution found. */
703 return 0;
704
705 write_string (abbr);
706 if (tags)
707 {
708 /* If there are ABI tags on the abbreviation, it becomes
709 a substitution candidate. */
710 write_abi_tags (tags);
711 add_substitution (node);
712 }
713 return 1;
714}
715
716/* Returns whether DECL's symbol name should be the plain unqualified-id
717 rather than a more complicated mangled name. */
718
719static bool
720unmangled_name_p (const tree decl)
721{
722 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
723 {
724 /* The names of `extern "C"' functions are not mangled. */
725 return (DECL_EXTERN_C_FUNCTION_P (decl)
726 /* But overloaded operator names *are* mangled. */
727 && !DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl));
728 }
729 else if (VAR_P (decl))
730 {
731 /* static variables are mangled. */
732 if (!DECL_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE_P (decl))
733 return false;
734
735 /* extern "C" declarations aren't mangled. */
736 if (DECL_EXTERN_C_P (decl))
737 return true;
738
739 /* Other variables at non-global scope are mangled. */
740 if (CP_DECL_CONTEXT (decl) != global_namespace)
741 return false;
742
743 /* Variable template instantiations are mangled. */
744 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
745 && variable_template_p (DECL_TI_TEMPLATE (decl)))
746 return false;
747
748 /* Declarations with ABI tags are mangled. */
749 if (get_abi_tags (decl))
750 return false;
751
752 /* The names of non-static global variables aren't mangled. */
753 return true;
754 }
755
756 return false;
757}
758
759/* TOP_LEVEL is true, if this is being called at outermost level of
760 mangling. It should be false when mangling a decl appearing in an
761 expression within some other mangling.
762
763 <mangled-name> ::= _Z <encoding> */
764
765static void
766write_mangled_name (const tree decl, bool top_level)
767{
768 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("mangled-name", decl);
769
770 check_abi_tags (decl);
771
772 if (unmangled_name_p (decl))
773 {
774 if (top_level)
775 write_string (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (decl)));
776 else
777 {
778 /* The standard notes: "The <encoding> of an extern "C"
779 function is treated like global-scope data, i.e. as its
780 <source-name> without a type." We cannot write
781 overloaded operators that way though, because it contains
782 characters invalid in assembler. */
783 write_string ("_Z");
784 write_source_name (DECL_NAME (decl));
785 }
786 }
787 else
788 {
789 write_string ("_Z");
790 write_encoding (decl);
791 }
792}
793
794/* Returns true if the return type of DECL is part of its signature, and
795 therefore its mangling. */
796
797bool
798mangle_return_type_p (tree decl)
799{
800 return (!DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl)
801 && !DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl)
802 && !DECL_CONV_FN_P (decl)
803 && decl_is_template_id (decl, NULL));
804}
805
806/* <encoding> ::= <function name> <bare-function-type>
807 ::= <data name> */
808
809static void
810write_encoding (const tree decl)
811{
812 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("encoding", decl);
813
814 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_EXTERN_C_FUNCTION_P (decl))
815 {
816 /* For overloaded operators write just the mangled name
817 without arguments. */
818 if (DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl))
819 write_name (decl, /*ignore_local_scope=*/0);
820 else
821 write_source_name (DECL_NAME (decl));
822 return;
823 }
824
825 write_name (decl, /*ignore_local_scope=*/0);
826 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
827 {
828 tree fn_type;
829 tree d;
830 bool tmpl = decl_is_template_id (decl, NULL);
831
832 if (tmpl)
833 {
834 fn_type = get_mostly_instantiated_function_type (decl);
835 /* FN_TYPE will not have parameter types for in-charge or
836 VTT parameters. Therefore, we pass NULL_TREE to
837 write_bare_function_type -- otherwise, it will get
838 confused about which artificial parameters to skip. */
839 d = NULL_TREE;
840 }
841 else
842 {
843 fn_type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
844 d = decl;
845 }
846
847 write_bare_function_type (fn_type,
848 mangle_return_type_p (decl),
849 d);
850 }
851}
852
853/* Lambdas can have a bit more context for mangling, specifically VAR_DECL
854 or PARM_DECL context, which doesn't belong in DECL_CONTEXT. */
855
856static tree
857decl_mangling_context (tree decl)
858{
859 tree tcontext = targetm.cxx.decl_mangling_context (decl);
860
861 if (tcontext != NULL_TREE)
862 return tcontext;
863
864 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TEMPLATE_DECL
865 && DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (decl))
866 decl = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (decl);
867
868 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
869 && LAMBDA_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
870 {
871 tree extra = LAMBDA_TYPE_EXTRA_SCOPE (TREE_TYPE (decl));
872 if (extra)
873 return extra;
874 }
875 else if (template_type_parameter_p (decl))
876 /* template type parms have no mangling context. */
877 return NULL_TREE;
878 return CP_DECL_CONTEXT (decl);
879}
880
881/* <name> ::= <unscoped-name>
882 ::= <unscoped-template-name> <template-args>
883 ::= <nested-name>
884 ::= <local-name>
885
886 If IGNORE_LOCAL_SCOPE is nonzero, this production of <name> is
887 called from <local-name>, which mangles the enclosing scope
888 elsewhere and then uses this function to mangle just the part
889 underneath the function scope. So don't use the <local-name>
890 production, to avoid an infinite recursion. */
891
892static void
893write_name (tree decl, const int ignore_local_scope)
894{
895 tree context;
896
897 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("name", decl);
898
899 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
900 {
901 /* In case this is a typedef, fish out the corresponding
902 TYPE_DECL for the main variant. */
903 decl = TYPE_NAME (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (decl)));
904 }
905
906 context = decl_mangling_context (decl);
907
908 gcc_assert (context != NULL_TREE);
909
910 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (7)
911 && ignore_local_scope
912 && TREE_CODE (context) == PARM_DECL)
913 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
914
915 /* A decl in :: or ::std scope is treated specially. The former is
916 mangled using <unscoped-name> or <unscoped-template-name>, the
917 latter with a special substitution. Also, a name that is
918 directly in a local function scope is also mangled with
919 <unscoped-name> rather than a full <nested-name>. */
920 if (context == global_namespace
921 || DECL_NAMESPACE_STD_P (context)
922 || (ignore_local_scope
923 && (TREE_CODE (context) == FUNCTION_DECL
924 || (abi_version_at_least (7)
925 && TREE_CODE (context) == PARM_DECL))))
926 {
927 tree template_info;
928 /* Is this a template instance? */
929 if (decl_is_template_id (decl, &template_info))
930 {
931 /* Yes: use <unscoped-template-name>. */
932 write_unscoped_template_name (TI_TEMPLATE (template_info));
933 write_template_args (TI_ARGS (template_info));
934 }
935 else
936 /* Everything else gets an <unqualified-name>. */
937 write_unscoped_name (decl);
938 }
939 else
940 {
941 /* Handle local names, unless we asked not to (that is, invoked
942 under <local-name>, to handle only the part of the name under
943 the local scope). */
944 if (!ignore_local_scope)
945 {
946 /* Scan up the list of scope context, looking for a
947 function. If we find one, this entity is in local
948 function scope. local_entity tracks context one scope
949 level down, so it will contain the element that's
950 directly in that function's scope, either decl or one of
951 its enclosing scopes. */
952 tree local_entity = decl;
953 while (context != global_namespace)
954 {
955 /* Make sure we're always dealing with decls. */
956 if (TYPE_P (context))
957 context = TYPE_NAME (context);
958 /* Is this a function? */
959 if (TREE_CODE (context) == FUNCTION_DECL
960 || TREE_CODE (context) == PARM_DECL)
961 {
962 /* Yes, we have local scope. Use the <local-name>
963 production for the innermost function scope. */
964 write_local_name (context, local_entity, decl);
965 return;
966 }
967 /* Up one scope level. */
968 local_entity = context;
969 context = decl_mangling_context (context);
970 }
971
972 /* No local scope found? Fall through to <nested-name>. */
973 }
974
975 /* Other decls get a <nested-name> to encode their scope. */
976 write_nested_name (decl);
977 }
978}
979
980/* <unscoped-name> ::= <unqualified-name>
981 ::= St <unqualified-name> # ::std:: */
982
983static void
984write_unscoped_name (const tree decl)
985{
986 tree context = decl_mangling_context (decl);
987
988 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("unscoped-name", decl);
989
990 /* Is DECL in ::std? */
991 if (DECL_NAMESPACE_STD_P (context))
992 {
993 write_string ("St");
994 write_unqualified_name (decl);
995 }
996 else
997 {
998 /* If not, it should be either in the global namespace, or directly
999 in a local function scope. A lambda can also be mangled in the
1000 scope of a default argument. */
1001 gcc_assert (context == global_namespace
1002 || TREE_CODE (context) == PARM_DECL
1003 || TREE_CODE (context) == FUNCTION_DECL);
1004
1005 write_unqualified_name (decl);
1006 }
1007}
1008
1009/* <unscoped-template-name> ::= <unscoped-name>
1010 ::= <substitution> */
1011
1012static void
1013write_unscoped_template_name (const tree decl)
1014{
1015 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("unscoped-template-name", decl);
1016
1017 if (find_substitution (decl))
1018 return;
1019 write_unscoped_name (decl);
1020 add_substitution (decl);
1021}
1022
1023/* Write the nested name, including CV-qualifiers, of DECL.
1024
1025 <nested-name> ::= N [<CV-qualifiers>] [<ref-qualifier>] <prefix> <unqualified-name> E
1026 ::= N [<CV-qualifiers>] [<ref-qualifier>] <template-prefix> <template-args> E
1027
1028 <ref-qualifier> ::= R # & ref-qualifier
1029 ::= O # && ref-qualifier
1030 <CV-qualifiers> ::= [r] [V] [K] */
1031
1032static void
1033write_nested_name (const tree decl)
1034{
1035 tree template_info;
1036
1037 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("nested-name", decl);
1038
1039 write_char ('N');
1040
1041 /* Write CV-qualifiers, if this is a member function. */
1042 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
1043 && DECL_NONSTATIC_MEMBER_FUNCTION_P (decl))
1044 {
1045 if (DECL_VOLATILE_MEMFUNC_P (decl))
1046 write_char ('V');
1047 if (DECL_CONST_MEMFUNC_P (decl))
1048 write_char ('K');
1049 if (FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
1050 {
1051 if (FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED (TREE_TYPE (decl)))
1052 write_char ('O');
1053 else
1054 write_char ('R');
1055 }
1056 }
1057
1058 /* Is this a template instance? */
1059 if (decl_is_template_id (decl, &template_info))
1060 {
1061 /* Yes, use <template-prefix>. */
1062 write_template_prefix (decl);
1063 write_template_args (TI_ARGS (template_info));
1064 }
1065 else if ((!abi_version_at_least (10) || TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
1066 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == TYPENAME_TYPE)
1067 {
1068 tree name = TYPENAME_TYPE_FULLNAME (TREE_TYPE (decl));
1069 if (TREE_CODE (name) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
1070 {
1071 write_template_prefix (decl);
1072 write_template_args (TREE_OPERAND (name, 1));
1073 }
1074 else
1075 {
1076 write_prefix (decl_mangling_context (decl));
1077 write_unqualified_name (decl);
1078 }
1079 }
1080 else
1081 {
1082 /* No, just use <prefix> */
1083 write_prefix (decl_mangling_context (decl));
1084 write_unqualified_name (decl);
1085 }
1086 write_char ('E');
1087}
1088
1089/* <prefix> ::= <prefix> <unqualified-name>
1090 ::= <template-param>
1091 ::= <template-prefix> <template-args>
1092 ::= <decltype>
1093 ::= # empty
1094 ::= <substitution> */
1095
1096static void
1097write_prefix (const tree node)
1098{
1099 tree decl;
1100 /* Non-NULL if NODE represents a template-id. */
1101 tree template_info = NULL;
1102
1103 if (node == NULL
1104 || node == global_namespace)
1105 return;
1106
1107 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("prefix", node);
1108
1109 if (TREE_CODE (node) == DECLTYPE_TYPE)
1110 {
1111 write_type (node);
1112 return;
1113 }
1114
1115 if (find_substitution (node))
1116 return;
1117
1118 if (DECL_P (node))
1119 {
1120 /* If this is a function or parm decl, that means we've hit function
1121 scope, so this prefix must be for a local name. In this
1122 case, we're under the <local-name> production, which encodes
1123 the enclosing function scope elsewhere. So don't continue
1124 here. */
1125 if (TREE_CODE (node) == FUNCTION_DECL
1126 || TREE_CODE (node) == PARM_DECL)
1127 return;
1128
1129 decl = node;
1130 decl_is_template_id (decl, &template_info);
1131 }
1132 else
1133 {
1134 /* Node is a type. */
1135 decl = TYPE_NAME (node);
1136 if (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_ID_P (node))
1137 template_info = TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (node);
1138 }
1139
1140 if (TREE_CODE (node) == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM)
1141 write_template_param (node);
1142 else if (template_info != NULL)
1143 /* Templated. */
1144 {
1145 write_template_prefix (decl);
1146 write_template_args (TI_ARGS (template_info));
1147 }
1148 else if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == TYPENAME_TYPE)
1149 {
1150 tree name = TYPENAME_TYPE_FULLNAME (TREE_TYPE (decl));
1151 if (TREE_CODE (name) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
1152 {
1153 write_template_prefix (decl);
1154 write_template_args (TREE_OPERAND (name, 1));
1155 }
1156 else
1157 {
1158 write_prefix (decl_mangling_context (decl));
1159 write_unqualified_name (decl);
1160 }
1161 }
1162 else
1163 /* Not templated. */
1164 {
1165 write_prefix (decl_mangling_context (decl));
1166 write_unqualified_name (decl);
1167 if (VAR_P (decl)
1168 || TREE_CODE (decl) == FIELD_DECL)
1169 {
1170 /* <data-member-prefix> := <member source-name> M */
1171 write_char ('M');
1172 return;
1173 }
1174 }
1175
1176 add_substitution (node);
1177}
1178
1179/* <template-prefix> ::= <prefix> <template component>
1180 ::= <template-param>
1181 ::= <substitution> */
1182
1183static void
1184write_template_prefix (const tree node)
1185{
1186 tree decl = DECL_P (node) ? node : TYPE_NAME (node);
1187 tree type = DECL_P (node) ? TREE_TYPE (node) : node;
1188 tree context = decl_mangling_context (decl);
1189 tree template_info;
1190 tree templ;
1191 tree substitution;
1192
1193 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("template-prefix", node);
1194
1195 /* Find the template decl. */
1196 if (decl_is_template_id (decl, &template_info))
1197 templ = TI_TEMPLATE (template_info);
1198 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == TYPENAME_TYPE)
1199 /* For a typename type, all we have is the name. */
1200 templ = DECL_NAME (decl);
1201 else
1202 {
1203 gcc_assert (CLASSTYPE_TEMPLATE_ID_P (type));
1204
1205 templ = TYPE_TI_TEMPLATE (type);
1206 }
1207
1208 /* For a member template, though, the template name for the
1209 innermost name must have all the outer template levels
1210 instantiated. For instance, consider
1211
1212 template<typename T> struct Outer {
1213 template<typename U> struct Inner {};
1214 };
1215
1216 The template name for `Inner' in `Outer<int>::Inner<float>' is
1217 `Outer<int>::Inner<U>'. In g++, we don't instantiate the template
1218 levels separately, so there's no TEMPLATE_DECL available for this
1219 (there's only `Outer<T>::Inner<U>').
1220
1221 In order to get the substitutions right, we create a special
1222 TREE_LIST to represent the substitution candidate for a nested
1223 template. The TREE_PURPOSE is the template's context, fully
1224 instantiated, and the TREE_VALUE is the TEMPLATE_DECL for the inner
1225 template.
1226
1227 So, for the example above, `Outer<int>::Inner' is represented as a
1228 substitution candidate by a TREE_LIST whose purpose is `Outer<int>'
1229 and whose value is `Outer<T>::Inner<U>'. */
1230 if (context && TYPE_P (context))
1231 substitution = build_tree_list (context, templ);
1232 else
1233 substitution = templ;
1234
1235 if (find_substitution (substitution))
1236 return;
1237
1238 if (TREE_TYPE (templ)
1239 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (templ)) == TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM)
1240 write_template_param (TREE_TYPE (templ));
1241 else
1242 {
1243 write_prefix (context);
1244 write_unqualified_name (decl);
1245 }
1246
1247 add_substitution (substitution);
1248}
1249
1250/* As the list of identifiers for the structured binding declaration
1251 DECL is likely gone, try to recover the DC <source-name>+ E portion
1252 from its mangled name. Return pointer to the DC and set len to
1253 the length up to and including the terminating E. On failure
1254 return NULL. */
1255
1256static const char *
1257find_decomp_unqualified_name (tree decl, size_t *len)
1258{
1259 const char *p = IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl));
1260 const char *end = p + IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl));
1261 bool nested = false;
1262 if (strncmp (p, "_Z", 2))
1263 return NULL;
1264 p += 2;
1265 if (!strncmp (p, "St", 2))
1266 p += 2;
1267 else if (*p == 'N')
1268 {
1269 nested = true;
1270 ++p;
1271 while (ISDIGIT (p[0]))
1272 {
1273 char *e;
1274 long num = strtol (p, &e, 10);
1275 if (num >= 1 && num < end - e)
1276 p = e + num;
1277 else
1278 break;
1279 }
1280 }
1281 if (strncmp (p, "DC", 2))
1282 return NULL;
1283 if (nested)
1284 {
1285 if (end[-1] != 'E')
1286 return NULL;
1287 --end;
1288 }
1289 if (end[-1] != 'E')
1290 return NULL;
1291 *len = end - p;
1292 return p;
1293}
1294
1295/* We don't need to handle thunks, vtables, or VTTs here. Those are
1296 mangled through special entry points.
1297
1298 <unqualified-name> ::= <operator-name>
1299 ::= <special-name>
1300 ::= <source-name>
1301 ::= <unnamed-type-name>
1302 ::= <local-source-name>
1303
1304 <local-source-name> ::= L <source-name> <discriminator> */
1305
1306static void
1307write_unqualified_id (tree identifier)
1308{
1309 if (IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (identifier))
1310 write_conversion_operator_name (TREE_TYPE (identifier));
1311 else if (IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (identifier))
1312 {
1313 int i;
1314 const char *mangled_name = NULL;
1315
1316 /* Unfortunately, there is no easy way to go from the
1317 name of the operator back to the corresponding tree
1318 code. */
1319 for (i = 0; i < MAX_TREE_CODES; ++i)
1320 if (operator_name_info[i].identifier == identifier)
1321 {
1322 /* The ABI says that we prefer binary operator
1323 names to unary operator names. */
1324 if (operator_name_info[i].arity == 2)
1325 {
1326 mangled_name = operator_name_info[i].mangled_name;
1327 break;
1328 }
1329 else if (!mangled_name)
1330 mangled_name = operator_name_info[i].mangled_name;
1331 }
1332 else if (assignment_operator_name_info[i].identifier
1333 == identifier)
1334 {
1335 mangled_name
1336 = assignment_operator_name_info[i].mangled_name;
1337 break;
1338 }
1339 write_string (mangled_name);
1340 }
1341 else if (UDLIT_OPER_P (identifier))
1342 write_literal_operator_name (identifier);
1343 else
1344 write_source_name (identifier);
1345}
1346
1347static void
1348write_unqualified_name (tree decl)
1349{
1350 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("unqualified-name", decl);
1351
1352 if (identifier_p (decl))
1353 {
1354 write_unqualified_id (decl);
1355 return;
1356 }
1357
1358 bool found = false;
1359
1360 if (DECL_NAME (decl) == NULL_TREE)
1361 {
1362 found = true;
1363 gcc_assert (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME_SET_P (decl));
1364 const char *decomp_str = NULL;
1365 size_t decomp_len = 0;
1366 if (VAR_P (decl)
1367 && DECL_DECOMPOSITION_P (decl)
1368 && DECL_NAME (decl) == NULL_TREE
1369 && DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl))
1370 decomp_str = find_decomp_unqualified_name (decl, &decomp_len);
1371 if (decomp_str)
1372 write_chars (decomp_str, decomp_len);
1373 else
1374 write_source_name (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl));
1375 }
1376 else if (DECL_DECLARES_FUNCTION_P (decl))
1377 {
1378 found = true;
1379 if (DECL_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl))
1380 write_special_name_constructor (decl);
1381 else if (DECL_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl))
1382 write_special_name_destructor (decl);
1383 else if (DECL_CONV_FN_P (decl))
1384 {
1385 /* Conversion operator. Handle it right here.
1386 <operator> ::= cv <type> */
1387 tree type;
1388 if (decl_is_template_id (decl, NULL))
1389 {
1390 tree fn_type;
1391 fn_type = get_mostly_instantiated_function_type (decl);
1392 type = TREE_TYPE (fn_type);
1393 }
1394 else if (FNDECL_USED_AUTO (decl))
1395 type = (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (decl)->language
1396 ->x_auto_return_pattern);
1397 else
1398 type = DECL_CONV_FN_TYPE (decl);
1399 write_conversion_operator_name (type);
1400 }
1401 else if (DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl))
1402 {
1403 operator_name_info_t *oni;
1404 if (DECL_ASSIGNMENT_OPERATOR_P (decl))
1405 oni = assignment_operator_name_info;
1406 else
1407 oni = operator_name_info;
1408
1409 write_string (oni[DECL_OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_P (decl)].mangled_name);
1410 }
1411 else if (UDLIT_OPER_P (DECL_NAME (decl)))
1412 write_literal_operator_name (DECL_NAME (decl));
1413 else
1414 found = false;
1415 }
1416
1417 if (found)
1418 /* OK */;
1419 else if (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl) && ! TREE_PUBLIC (decl)
1420 && DECL_NAMESPACE_SCOPE_P (decl)
1421 && decl_linkage (decl) == lk_internal)
1422 {
1423 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("local-source-name", decl);
1424 write_char ('L');
1425 write_source_name (DECL_NAME (decl));
1426 /* The default discriminator is 1, and that's all we ever use,
1427 so there's no code to output one here. */
1428 }
1429 else
1430 {
1431 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
1432
1433 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
1434 && TYPE_UNNAMED_P (type))
1435 write_unnamed_type_name (type);
1436 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
1437 && LAMBDA_TYPE_P (type))
1438 write_closure_type_name (type);
1439 else
1440 write_source_name (DECL_NAME (decl));
1441 }
1442
1443 /* We use the ABI tags from the primary class template, ignoring tags on any
1444 specializations. This is necessary because C++ doesn't require a
1445 specialization to be declared before it is used unless the use requires a
1446 complete type, but we need to get the tags right on incomplete types as
1447 well. */
1448 if (tree tmpl = most_general_template (decl))
1449 {
1450 tree res = DECL_TEMPLATE_RESULT (tmpl);
1451 if (res == NULL_TREE)
1452 /* UNBOUND_CLASS_TEMPLATE. */;
1453 else if (DECL_DECLARES_TYPE_P (decl))
1454 decl = res;
1455 else if (any_abi_below (11))
1456 {
1457 /* ABI v10 implicit tags on the template. */
1458 tree mtags = missing_abi_tags (res);
1459 /* Explicit tags on the template. */
1460 tree ttags = get_abi_tags (res);
1461 /* Tags on the instantiation. */
1462 tree dtags = get_abi_tags (decl);
1463
1464 if (mtags && abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (10))
1465 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
1466
1467 /* Add the v10 tags to the explicit tags now. */
1468 mtags = chainon (mtags, ttags);
1469
1470 if (!G.need_abi_warning
1471 && abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (11)
1472 && !equal_abi_tags (dtags, mtags))
1473 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
1474
1475 if (!abi_version_at_least (10))
1476 /* In abi <10, we only got the explicit tags. */
1477 decl = res;
1478 else if (flag_abi_version == 10)
1479 {
1480 /* In ABI 10, we want explict and implicit tags. */
1481 write_abi_tags (mtags);
1482 return;
1483 }
1484 }
1485 }
1486
1487 tree tags = get_abi_tags (decl);
1488 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL && DECL_CONV_FN_P (decl)
1489 && any_abi_below (11))
1490 if (tree mtags = missing_abi_tags (decl))
1491 {
1492 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (11))
1493 G.need_abi_warning = true;
1494 if (!abi_version_at_least (11))
1495 tags = chainon (mtags, tags);
1496 }
1497 write_abi_tags (tags);
1498}

1509/* Non-terminal <source-name>. IDENTIFIER is an IDENTIFIER_NODE.
1510
1511 <source-name> ::= </length/ number> <identifier> */
1512
1513static void
1514write_source_name (tree identifier)
1515{
1516 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("source-name", identifier);
1517
1518 /* Never write the whole template-id name including the template
1519 arguments; we only want the template name. */
1520 if (IDENTIFIER_TEMPLATE (identifier))
1521 identifier = IDENTIFIER_TEMPLATE (identifier);
1522
1523 write_unsigned_number (IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (identifier));
1524 write_identifier (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (identifier));
1525}
1526
1527/* Compare two TREE_STRINGs like strcmp. */
1528
1529int
1530tree_string_cmp (const void *p1, const void *p2)
1531{
1532 if (p1 == p2)
1533 return 0;
1534 tree s1 = *(const tree*)p1;
1535 tree s2 = *(const tree*)p2;
1536 return strcmp (TREE_STRING_POINTER (s1),
1537 TREE_STRING_POINTER (s2));
1538}
1539
1540/* Return the TREE_LIST of TAGS as a sorted VEC. */
1541
1542static vec<tree, va_gc> *
1543sorted_abi_tags (tree tags)
1544{
1545 vec<tree, va_gc> * vec = make_tree_vector();
1546
1547 for (tree t = tags; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
1548 {
1549 if (ABI_TAG_IMPLICIT (t))
1550 continue;
1551 tree str = TREE_VALUE (t);
1552 vec_safe_push (vec, str);
1553 }
1554
1555 vec->qsort (tree_string_cmp);
1556
1557 return vec;
1558}
1559
1560/* ID is the name of a function or type with abi_tags attribute TAGS.
1561 Write out the name, suitably decorated. */
1562
1563static void
1564write_abi_tags (tree tags)
1565{
1566 if (tags == NULL_TREE)
1567 return;
1568
1569 vec<tree, va_gc> * vec = sorted_abi_tags (tags);
1570
1571 unsigned i; tree str;
1572 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (*vec, i, str)
1573 {
1574 write_string ("B");
1575 write_unsigned_number (TREE_STRING_LENGTH (str) - 1);
1576 write_identifier (TREE_STRING_POINTER (str));
1577 }
1578
1579 release_tree_vector (vec);
1580}
1581
1582/* Simplified unique_ptr clone to release a tree vec on exit. */
1583
1584struct releasing_vec
1585{
1586 typedef vec<tree, va_gc> vec_t;
1587
1588 releasing_vec (vec_t *v): v(v) { }
1589 releasing_vec (): v(make_tree_vector ()) { }
1590
1591 vec_t &operator* () const { return *v; }
1592 vec_t *operator-> () const { return v; }
1593 vec_t *get () const { return v; }
1594 operator vec_t *() const { return v; }
1595 tree& operator[] (unsigned i) const { return (*v)[i]; }
1596
1597 ~releasing_vec() { release_tree_vector (v); }
1598private:
1599 vec_t *v;
1600};
1601
1602/* True iff the TREE_LISTS T1 and T2 of ABI tags are equivalent. */
1603
1604static bool
1605equal_abi_tags (tree t1, tree t2)
1606{
1607 releasing_vec v1 = sorted_abi_tags (t1);
1608 releasing_vec v2 = sorted_abi_tags (t2);
1609
1610 unsigned len1 = v1->length();
1611 if (len1 != v2->length())
1612 return false;
1613 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len1; ++i)
1614 if (tree_string_cmp (v1[i], v2[i]) != 0)
1615 return false;
1616 return true;
1617}

1642/* Return how many unnamed types precede TYPE in its enclosing class. */
1643
1644static int
1645nested_anon_class_index (tree type)
1646{
1647 int index = 0;
1648 tree member = TYPE_FIELDS (TYPE_CONTEXT (type));
1649 for (; member; member = DECL_CHAIN (member))
1650 if (DECL_IMPLICIT_TYPEDEF_P (member))
1651 {
1652 tree memtype = TREE_TYPE (member);
1653 if (memtype == type)
1654 return index;
1655 else if (TYPE_UNNAMED_P (memtype))
1656 ++index;
1657 }
1658
1659 gcc_unreachable ();
1660}

1662/* <unnamed-type-name> ::= Ut [ <nonnegative number> ] _ */
1663
1664static void
1665write_unnamed_type_name (const tree type)
1666{
1667 int discriminator;
1668 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("unnamed-type-name", type);
1669
1670 if (TYPE_FUNCTION_SCOPE_P (type))
1671 discriminator = local_class_index (type);
1672 else if (TYPE_CLASS_SCOPE_P (type))
1673 discriminator = nested_anon_class_index (type);
1674 else
1675 {
1676 gcc_assert (no_linkage_check (type, /*relaxed_p=*/true));
1677 /* Just use the old mangling at namespace scope. */
1678 write_source_name (TYPE_IDENTIFIER (type));
1679 return;
1680 }
1681
1682 write_string ("Ut");
1683 write_compact_number (discriminator);
1684}

1686/* <closure-type-name> ::= Ul <lambda-sig> E [ <nonnegative number> ] _
1687 <lambda-sig> ::= <parameter type>+ # Parameter types or "v" if the lambda has no parameters */
1688
1689static void
1690write_closure_type_name (const tree type)
1691{
1692 tree fn = lambda_function (type);
1693 tree lambda = CLASSTYPE_LAMBDA_EXPR (type);
1694 tree parms = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (TREE_TYPE (fn));
1695
1696 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("closure-type-name", type);
1697
1698 write_string ("Ul");
1699 write_method_parms (parms, /*method_p=*/1, fn);
1700 write_char ('E');
1701 write_compact_number (LAMBDA_EXPR_DISCRIMINATOR (lambda));
1702}
1703
1704/* Convert NUMBER to ascii using base BASE and generating at least
1705 MIN_DIGITS characters. BUFFER points to the _end_ of the buffer
1706 into which to store the characters. Returns the number of
1707 characters generated (these will be laid out in advance of where
1708 BUFFER points). */
1709
1710static int
1711hwint_to_ascii (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT number, const unsigned int base,
1712 char *buffer, const unsigned int min_digits)
1713{
1714 static const char base_digits[] = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ";
1715 unsigned digits = 0;
1716
1717 while (number)
1718 {
1719 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT d = number / base;
1720
1721 *--buffer = base_digits[number - d * base];
1722 digits++;
1723 number = d;
1724 }
1725 while (digits < min_digits)
1726 {
1727 *--buffer = base_digits[0];
1728 digits++;
1729 }
1730 return digits;
1731}
1732
1733/* Non-terminal <number>.
1734
1735 <number> ::= [n] </decimal integer/> */
1736
1737static void
1738write_number (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT number, const int unsigned_p,
1739 const unsigned int base)
1740{
1741 char buffer[sizeof (HOST_WIDE_INT) * 8];
1742 unsigned count = 0;
1743
1744 if (!unsigned_p && (HOST_WIDE_INT) number < 0)
1745 {
1746 write_char ('n');
1747 number = -((HOST_WIDE_INT) number);
1748 }
1749 count = hwint_to_ascii (number, base, buffer + sizeof (buffer), 1);
1750 write_chars (buffer + sizeof (buffer) - count, count);
1751}
1752
1753/* Write out an integral CST in decimal. Most numbers are small, and
1754 representable in a HOST_WIDE_INT. Occasionally we'll have numbers
1755 bigger than that, which we must deal with. */
1756
1757static inline void
1758write_integer_cst (const tree cst)
1759{
1760 int sign = tree_int_cst_sgn (cst);
1761 widest_int abs_value = wi::abs (wi::to_widest (cst));
1762 if (!wi::fits_uhwi_p (abs_value))
1763 {
1764 /* A bignum. We do this in chunks, each of which fits in a
1765 HOST_WIDE_INT. */
1766 char buffer[sizeof (HOST_WIDE_INT) * 8 * 2];
1767 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT chunk;
1768 unsigned chunk_digits;
1769 char *ptr = buffer + sizeof (buffer);
1770 unsigned count = 0;
1771 tree n, base, type;
1772 int done;
1773
1774 /* HOST_WIDE_INT must be at least 32 bits, so 10^9 is
1775 representable. */
1776 chunk = 1000000000;
1777 chunk_digits = 9;
1778
1779 if (sizeof (HOST_WIDE_INT) >= 8)
1780 {
1781 /* It is at least 64 bits, so 10^18 is representable. */
1782 chunk_digits = 18;
1783 chunk *= chunk;
1784 }
1785
1786 type = c_common_signed_or_unsigned_type (1, TREE_TYPE (cst));
1787 base = build_int_cstu (type, chunk);
1788 n = wide_int_to_tree (type, cst);
1789
1790 if (sign < 0)
1791 {
1792 write_char ('n');
1793 n = fold_build1_loc (input_location, NEGATE_EXPR, type, n);
1794 }
1795 do
1796 {
1797 tree d = fold_build2_loc (input_location, FLOOR_DIV_EXPR, type, n, base);
1798 tree tmp = fold_build2_loc (input_location, MULT_EXPR, type, d, base);
1799 unsigned c;
1800
1801 done = integer_zerop (d);
1802 tmp = fold_build2_loc (input_location, MINUS_EXPR, type, n, tmp);
1803 c = hwint_to_ascii (TREE_INT_CST_LOW (tmp), 10, ptr,
1804 done ? 1 : chunk_digits);
1805 ptr -= c;
1806 count += c;
1807 n = d;
1808 }
1809 while (!done);
1810 write_chars (ptr, count);
1811 }
1812 else
1813 {
1814 /* A small num. */
1815 if (sign < 0)
1816 write_char ('n');
1817 write_unsigned_number (abs_value.to_uhwi ());
1818 }
1819}
1820
1821/* Write out a floating-point literal.
1822
1823 "Floating-point literals are encoded using the bit pattern of the
1824 target processor's internal representation of that number, as a
1825 fixed-length lowercase hexadecimal string, high-order bytes first
1826 (even if the target processor would store low-order bytes first).
1827 The "n" prefix is not used for floating-point literals; the sign
1828 bit is encoded with the rest of the number.
1829
1830 Here are some examples, assuming the IEEE standard representation
1831 for floating point numbers. (Spaces are for readability, not
1832 part of the encoding.)
1833
1834 1.0f Lf 3f80 0000 E
1835 -1.0f Lf bf80 0000 E
1836 1.17549435e-38f Lf 0080 0000 E
1837 1.40129846e-45f Lf 0000 0001 E
1838 0.0f Lf 0000 0000 E"
1839
1840 Caller is responsible for the Lx and the E. */
1841static void
1842write_real_cst (const tree value)
1843{
1844 long target_real[4]; /* largest supported float */
1845 /* Buffer for eight hex digits in a 32-bit number but big enough
1846 even for 64-bit long to avoid warnings. */
1847 char buffer[17];
1848 int i, limit, dir;
1849
1850 tree type = TREE_TYPE (value);
1851 int words = GET_MODE_BITSIZE (TYPE_MODE (type)) / 32;
1852
1853 real_to_target (target_real, &TREE_REAL_CST (value),
1854 TYPE_MODE (type));
1855
1856 /* The value in target_real is in the target word order,
1857 so we must write it out backward if that happens to be
1858 little-endian. write_number cannot be used, it will
1859 produce uppercase. */
1860 if (FLOAT_WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
1861 i = 0, limit = words, dir = 1;
1862 else
1863 i = words - 1, limit = -1, dir = -1;
1864
1865 for (; i != limit; i += dir)
1866 {
1867 sprintf (buffer, "%08lx", (unsigned long) target_real[i]);
1868 write_chars (buffer, 8);
1869 }
1870}

1873
1874 <identifier> ::= </unqualified source code identifier> */
1875
1876static void
1877write_identifier (const char *identifier)
1878{
1879 MANGLE_TRACE ("identifier", identifier);
1880 write_string (identifier);

1883/* Handle constructor productions of non-terminal <special-name>.
1884 CTOR is a constructor FUNCTION_DECL.
1885
1886 <special-name> ::= C1 # complete object constructor
1887 ::= C2 # base object constructor
1888 ::= C3 # complete object allocating constructor
1889
1890 Currently, allocating constructors are never used. */
1891
1892static void
1893write_special_name_constructor (const tree ctor)
1894{
1895 write_char ('C');
1896 bool new_inh = (flag_new_inheriting_ctors
1897 && DECL_INHERITED_CTOR (ctor));
1898 if (new_inh)
1899 write_char ('I');
1900 if (DECL_BASE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (ctor))
1901 write_char ('2');
1902 /* This is the old-style "[unified]" constructor.
1903 In some cases, we may emit this function and call
1904 it from the clones in order to share code and save space. */
1905 else if (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (ctor))
1906 write_char ('4');
1907 else
1908 {
1909 gcc_assert (DECL_COMPLETE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (ctor));
1910 write_char ('1');
1911 }
1912 if (new_inh)
1913 write_type (DECL_INHERITED_CTOR_BASE (ctor));
1914}
1915
1916/* Handle destructor productions of non-terminal <special-name>.
1917 DTOR is a destructor FUNCTION_DECL.
1918
1919 <special-name> ::= D0 # deleting (in-charge) destructor
1920 ::= D1 # complete object (in-charge) destructor
1921 ::= D2 # base object (not-in-charge) destructor */
1922
1923static void
1924write_special_name_destructor (const tree dtor)
1925{
1926 if (DECL_DELETING_DESTRUCTOR_P (dtor))
1927 write_string ("D0");
1928 else if (DECL_BASE_DESTRUCTOR_P (dtor))
1929 write_string ("D2");
1930 else if (DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_DESTRUCTOR_P (dtor))
1931 /* This is the old-style "[unified]" destructor.
1932 In some cases, we may emit this function and call
1933 it from the clones in order to share code and save space. */
1934 write_string ("D4");
1935 else
1936 {
1937 gcc_assert (DECL_COMPLETE_DESTRUCTOR_P (dtor));
1938 write_string ("D1");
1939 }
1940}
1941
1942/* Scan the vector of local classes and return how many others with the
1943 same name (or same no name) and context precede ENTITY. */
1944
1945static int
1946local_class_index (tree entity)
1947{
1948 int ix, discriminator = 0;
1949 tree name = (TYPE_UNNAMED_P (entity) ? NULL_TREE
1950 : TYPE_IDENTIFIER (entity));
1951 tree ctx = TYPE_CONTEXT (entity);
1952 for (ix = 0; ; ix++)
1953 {
1954 tree type = (*local_classes)[ix];
1955 if (type == entity)
1956 return discriminator;
1957 if (TYPE_CONTEXT (type) == ctx
1958 && (name ? TYPE_IDENTIFIER (type) == name
1959 : TYPE_UNNAMED_P (type)))
1960 ++discriminator;
1961 }
1962 gcc_unreachable ();
1963}
1964
1965/* Return the discriminator for ENTITY appearing inside
1966 FUNCTION. The discriminator is the lexical ordinal of VAR among
1967 entities with the same name in the same FUNCTION. */
1968
1969static int
1970discriminator_for_local_entity (tree entity)
1971{
1972 if (DECL_DISCRIMINATOR_P (entity))
1973 {
1974 if (DECL_DISCRIMINATOR_SET_P (entity))
1975 return DECL_DISCRIMINATOR (entity);
1976 else
1977 /* The first entity with a particular name doesn't get
1978 DECL_DISCRIMINATOR set up. */
1979 return 0;
1980 }
1981 else if (TREE_CODE (entity) == TYPE_DECL)
1982 {
1983 /* Scan the list of local classes. */
1984 entity = TREE_TYPE (entity);
1985
1986 /* Lambdas and unnamed types have their own discriminators. */
1987 if (LAMBDA_TYPE_P (entity) || TYPE_UNNAMED_P (entity))
1988 return 0;
1989
1990 return local_class_index (entity);
1991 }
1992 else
1993 gcc_unreachable ();
1994}
1995
1996/* Return the discriminator for STRING, a string literal used inside
1997 FUNCTION. The discriminator is the lexical ordinal of STRING among
1998 string literals used in FUNCTION. */
1999
2000static int
2001discriminator_for_string_literal (tree /*function*/,
2002 tree /*string*/)
2003{
2004 /* For now, we don't discriminate amongst string literals. */
2005 return 0;
2006}
2007
2008/* <discriminator> := _ <number> # when number < 10
2009 := __ <number> _ # when number >= 10
2010
2011 The discriminator is used only for the second and later occurrences
2012 of the same name within a single function. In this case <number> is
2013 n - 2, if this is the nth occurrence, in lexical order. */
2014
2015static void
2016write_discriminator (const int discriminator)
2017{
2018 /* If discriminator is zero, don't write anything. Otherwise... */
2019 if (discriminator > 0)
2020 {
2021 write_char ('_');
2022 if (discriminator - 1 >= 10)
2023 {
2024 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (11))
2025 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2026 if (abi_version_at_least (11))
2027 write_char ('_');
2028 }
2029 write_unsigned_number (discriminator - 1);
2030 if (abi_version_at_least (11) && discriminator - 1 >= 10)
2031 write_char ('_');
2032 }
2033}
2034
2035/* Mangle the name of a function-scope entity. FUNCTION is the
2036 FUNCTION_DECL for the enclosing function, or a PARM_DECL for lambdas in
2037 default argument scope. ENTITY is the decl for the entity itself.
2038 LOCAL_ENTITY is the entity that's directly scoped in FUNCTION_DECL,
2039 either ENTITY itself or an enclosing scope of ENTITY.
2040
2041 <local-name> := Z <function encoding> E <entity name> [<discriminator>]
2042 := Z <function encoding> E s [<discriminator>]
2043 := Z <function encoding> Ed [ <parameter number> ] _ <entity name> */
2044
2045static void
2046write_local_name (tree function, const tree local_entity,
2047 const tree entity)
2048{
2049 tree parm = NULL_TREE;
2050
2051 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("local-name", entity);
2052
2053 if (TREE_CODE (function) == PARM_DECL)
2054 {
2055 parm = function;
2056 function = DECL_CONTEXT (parm);
2057 }
2058
2059 write_char ('Z');
2060 write_encoding (function);
2061 write_char ('E');
2062
2063 /* For this purpose, parameters are numbered from right-to-left. */
2064 if (parm)
2065 {
2066 tree t;
2067 int i = 0;
2068 for (t = DECL_ARGUMENTS (function); t; t = DECL_CHAIN (t))
2069 {
2070 if (t == parm)
2071 i = 1;
2072 else if (i)
2073 ++i;
2074 }
2075 write_char ('d');
2076 write_compact_number (i - 1);
2077 }
2078
2079 if (TREE_CODE (entity) == STRING_CST)
2080 {
2081 write_char ('s');
2082 write_discriminator (discriminator_for_string_literal (function,
2083 entity));
2084 }
2085 else
2086 {
2087 /* Now the <entity name>. Let write_name know its being called
2088 from <local-name>, so it doesn't try to process the enclosing
2089 function scope again. */
2090 write_name (entity, /*ignore_local_scope=*/1);
2091 write_discriminator (discriminator_for_local_entity (local_entity));
2092 }
2093}
2094
2095/* Non-terminals <type> and <CV-qualifier>.
2096
2097 <type> ::= <builtin-type>
2098 ::= <function-type>
2099 ::= <class-enum-type>
2100 ::= <array-type>
2101 ::= <pointer-to-member-type>
2102 ::= <template-param>
2103 ::= <substitution>
2104 ::= <CV-qualifier>
2105 ::= P <type> # pointer-to
2106 ::= R <type> # reference-to
2107 ::= C <type> # complex pair (C 2000)
2108 ::= G <type> # imaginary (C 2000) [not supported]
2109 ::= U <source-name> <type> # vendor extended type qualifier
2110
2111 C++0x extensions
2112
2113 <type> ::= RR <type> # rvalue reference-to
2114 <type> ::= Dt <expression> # decltype of an id-expression or
2115 # class member access
2116 <type> ::= DT <expression> # decltype of an expression
2117 <type> ::= Dn # decltype of nullptr
2118
2119 TYPE is a type node. */
2120
2121static void
2122write_type (tree type)
2123{
2124 /* This gets set to nonzero if TYPE turns out to be a (possibly
2125 CV-qualified) builtin type. */
2126 int is_builtin_type = 0;
2127
2128 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("type", type);
2129
2130 if (type == error_mark_node)
2131 return;
2132
2133 type = canonicalize_for_substitution (type);
2134 if (find_substitution (type))
2135 return;
2136
2137
2138 if (write_CV_qualifiers_for_type (type) > 0)
2139 /* If TYPE was CV-qualified, we just wrote the qualifiers; now
2140 mangle the unqualified type. The recursive call is needed here
2141 since both the qualified and unqualified types are substitution
2142 candidates. */
2143 {
2144 tree t = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
2145 if (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (t) && !OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (t))
2146 {
2147 tree attrs = NULL_TREE;
2148 if (tx_safe_fn_type_p (type))
2149 attrs = tree_cons (get_identifier ("transaction_safe"),
2150 NULL_TREE, attrs);
2151 t = cp_build_type_attribute_variant (t, attrs);
2152 }
2153 gcc_assert (t != type);
2154 if (TREE_CODE (t) == FUNCTION_TYPE
2155 || TREE_CODE (t) == METHOD_TYPE)
2156 {
2157 t = build_ref_qualified_type (t, type_memfn_rqual (type));
2158 if (flag_noexcept_type)
2159 {
2160 tree r = TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (type);
2161 t = build_exception_variant (t, r);
2162 }
2163 if (abi_version_at_least (8)
2164 || type == TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type))
2165 /* Avoid adding the unqualified function type as a substitution. */
2166 write_function_type (t);
2167 else
2168 write_type (t);
2169 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (8))
2170 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2171 }
2172 else
2173 write_type (t);
2174 }
2175 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
2176 /* It is important not to use the TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT of TYPE here
2177 so that the cv-qualification of the element type is available
2178 in write_array_type. */
2179 write_array_type (type);
2180 else
2181 {
2182 tree type_orig = type;
2183
2184 /* See through any typedefs. */
2185 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
2186 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE
2187 || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
2188 {
2189 type = build_ref_qualified_type (type, type_memfn_rqual (type_orig));
2190 type = build_exception_variant (type,
2191 TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (type_orig));
2192 }
2193
2194 /* According to the C++ ABI, some library classes are passed the
2195 same as the scalar type of their single member and use the same
2196 mangling. */
2197 if (TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE && TYPE_TRANSPARENT_AGGR (type))
2198 type = TREE_TYPE (first_field (type));
2199
2200 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (type))
2201 write_pointer_to_member_type (type);
2202 else
2203 {
2204 /* Handle any target-specific fundamental types. */
2205 const char *target_mangling
2206 = targetm.mangle_type (type_orig);
2207
2208 if (target_mangling)
2209 {
2210 write_string (target_mangling);
2211 /* Add substitutions for types other than fundamental
2212 types. */
2213 if (!VOID_TYPE_P (type)
2214 && TREE_CODE (type) != INTEGER_TYPE
2215 && TREE_CODE (type) != REAL_TYPE
2216 && TREE_CODE (type) != BOOLEAN_TYPE)
2217 add_substitution (type);
2218 return;
2219 }
2220
2221 switch (TREE_CODE (type))
2222 {
2223 case VOID_TYPE:
2224 case BOOLEAN_TYPE:
2225 case INTEGER_TYPE: /* Includes wchar_t. */
2226 case REAL_TYPE:
2227 case FIXED_POINT_TYPE:
2228 {
2229 /* If this is a typedef, TYPE may not be one of
2230 the standard builtin type nodes, but an alias of one. Use
2231 TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT to get to the underlying builtin type. */
2232 write_builtin_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type));
2233 ++is_builtin_type;
2234 }
2235 break;
2236
2237 case COMPLEX_TYPE:
2238 write_char ('C');
2239 write_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
2240 break;
2241
2242 case FUNCTION_TYPE:
2243 case METHOD_TYPE:
2244 write_function_type (type);
2245 break;
2246
2247 case UNION_TYPE:
2248 case RECORD_TYPE:
2249 case ENUMERAL_TYPE:
2250 /* A pointer-to-member function is represented as a special
2251 RECORD_TYPE, so check for this first. */
2252 if (TYPE_PTRMEMFUNC_P (type))
2253 write_pointer_to_member_type (type);
2254 else
2255 write_class_enum_type (type);
2256 break;
2257
2258 case TYPENAME_TYPE:
2259 case UNBOUND_CLASS_TEMPLATE:
2260 /* We handle TYPENAME_TYPEs and UNBOUND_CLASS_TEMPLATEs like
2261 ordinary nested names. */
2262 write_nested_name (TYPE_STUB_DECL (type));
2263 break;
2264
2265 case POINTER_TYPE:
2266 case REFERENCE_TYPE:
2267 if (TYPE_PTR_P (type))
2268 write_char ('P');
2269 else if (TYPE_REF_IS_RVALUE (type))
2270 write_char ('O');
2271 else
2272 write_char ('R');
2273 {
2274 tree target = TREE_TYPE (type);
2275 /* Attribute const/noreturn are not reflected in mangling.
2276 We strip them here rather than at a lower level because
2277 a typedef or template argument can have function type
2278 with function-cv-quals (that use the same representation),
2279 but you can't have a pointer/reference to such a type. */
2280 if (TREE_CODE (target) == FUNCTION_TYPE)
2281 {
2282 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (5)
2283 && TYPE_QUALS (target) != TYPE_UNQUALIFIED)
2284 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2285 if (abi_version_at_least (5))
2286 target = build_qualified_type (target, TYPE_UNQUALIFIED);
2287 }
2288 write_type (target);
2289 }
2290 break;
2291
2292 case TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM:
2293 if (is_auto (type))
2294 {
2295 if (AUTO_IS_DECLTYPE (type))
2296 write_identifier ("Dc");
2297 else
2298 write_identifier ("Da");
2299 ++is_builtin_type;
2300 break;
2301 }
2302 /* fall through. */
2303 case TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX:
2304 write_template_param (type);
2305 break;
2306
2307 case TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM:
2308 write_template_template_param (type);
2309 break;
2310
2311 case BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM:
2312 write_template_template_param (type);
2313 write_template_args
2314 (TI_ARGS (TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_TEMPLATE_INFO (type)));
2315 break;
2316
2317 case VECTOR_TYPE:
2318 if (abi_version_at_least (4))
2319 {
2320 write_string ("Dv");
2321 /* Non-constant vector size would be encoded with
2322 _ expression, but we don't support that yet. */
2323 write_unsigned_number (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (type));
2324 write_char ('_');
2325 }
2326 else
2327 write_string ("U8__vector");
2328 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (4))
2329 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2330 write_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
2331 break;
2332
2333 case TYPE_PACK_EXPANSION:
2334 write_string ("Dp");
2335 write_type (PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN (type));
2336 break;
2337
2338 case DECLTYPE_TYPE:
2339 /* These shouldn't make it into mangling. */
2340 gcc_assert (!DECLTYPE_FOR_LAMBDA_CAPTURE (type)
2341 && !DECLTYPE_FOR_LAMBDA_PROXY (type));
2342
2343 /* In ABI <5, we stripped decltype of a plain decl. */
2344 if (DECLTYPE_TYPE_ID_EXPR_OR_MEMBER_ACCESS_P (type))
2345 {
2346 tree expr = DECLTYPE_TYPE_EXPR (type);
2347 tree etype = NULL_TREE;
2348 switch (TREE_CODE (expr))
2349 {
2350 case VAR_DECL:
2351 case PARM_DECL:
2352 case RESULT_DECL:
2353 case FUNCTION_DECL:
2354 case CONST_DECL:
2355 case TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX:
2356 etype = TREE_TYPE (expr);
2357 break;
2358
2359 default:
2360 break;
2361 }
2362
2363 if (etype && !type_uses_auto (etype))
2364 {
2365 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (5))
2366 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2367 if (!abi_version_at_least (5))
2368 {
2369 write_type (etype);
2370 return;
2371 }
2372 }
2373 }
2374
2375 write_char ('D');
2376 if (DECLTYPE_TYPE_ID_EXPR_OR_MEMBER_ACCESS_P (type))
2377 write_char ('t');
2378 else
2379 write_char ('T');
2380 ++cp_unevaluated_operand;
2381 write_expression (DECLTYPE_TYPE_EXPR (type));
2382 --cp_unevaluated_operand;
2383 write_char ('E');
2384 break;
2385
2386 case NULLPTR_TYPE:
2387 write_string ("Dn");
2388 if (abi_version_at_least (7))
2389 ++is_builtin_type;
2390 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (7))
2391 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2392 break;
2393
2394 case TYPEOF_TYPE:
2395 sorry ("mangling typeof, use decltype instead");
2396 break;
2397
2398 case UNDERLYING_TYPE:
2399 sorry ("mangling __underlying_type");
2400 break;
2401
2402 case LANG_TYPE:
2403 /* fall through. */
2404
2405 default:
2406 gcc_unreachable ();
2407 }
2408 }
2409 }
2410
2411 /* Types other than builtin types are substitution candidates. */
2412 if (!is_builtin_type)
2413 add_substitution (type);
2414}
2415
2416/* qsort callback for sorting a vector of attribute entries. */
2417
2418static int
2419attr_strcmp (const void *p1, const void *p2)
2420{
2421 tree a1 = *(const tree*)p1;
2422 tree a2 = *(const tree*)p2;
2423
2424 const attribute_spec *as1 = lookup_attribute_spec (get_attribute_name (a1));
2425 const attribute_spec *as2 = lookup_attribute_spec (get_attribute_name (a2));
2426
2427 return strcmp (as1->name, as2->name);
2428}
2429
2430/* Non-terminal <CV-qualifiers> for type nodes. Returns the number of
2431 CV-qualifiers written for TYPE.
2432
2433 <CV-qualifiers> ::= [r] [V] [K] */
2434
2435static int
2436write_CV_qualifiers_for_type (const tree type)
2437{
2438 int num_qualifiers = 0;
2439
2440 /* The order is specified by:
2441
2442 "In cases where multiple order-insensitive qualifiers are
2443 present, they should be ordered 'K' (closest to the base type),
2444 'V', 'r', and 'U' (farthest from the base type) ..." */
2445
2446 /* Mangle attributes that affect type identity as extended qualifiers.
2447
2448 We don't do this with classes and enums because their attributes
2449 are part of their definitions, not something added on. */
2450
2451 if (!OVERLOAD_TYPE_P (type))
2452 {
2453 auto_vec<tree> vec;
2454 for (tree a = TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (type); a; a = TREE_CHAIN (a))
2455 {
2456 tree name = get_attribute_name (a);
2457 const attribute_spec *as = lookup_attribute_spec (name);
2458 if (as && as->affects_type_identity
2459 && !is_attribute_p ("transaction_safe", name)
2460 && !is_attribute_p ("abi_tag", name))
2461 vec.safe_push (a);
2462 }
2463 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (10) && !vec.is_empty ())
2464 G.need_abi_warning = true;
2465 if (abi_version_at_least (10))
2466 {
2467 vec.qsort (attr_strcmp);
2468 while (!vec.is_empty())
2469 {
2470 tree a = vec.pop();
2471 const attribute_spec *as
2472 = lookup_attribute_spec (get_attribute_name (a));
2473
2474 write_char ('U');
2475 write_unsigned_number (strlen (as->name));
2476 write_string (as->name);
2477 if (TREE_VALUE (a))
2478 {
2479 write_char ('I');
2480 for (tree args = TREE_VALUE (a); args;
2481 args = TREE_CHAIN (args))
2482 {
2483 tree arg = TREE_VALUE (args);
2484 write_template_arg (arg);
2485 }
2486 write_char ('E');
2487 }
2488
2489 ++num_qualifiers;
2490 }
2491 }
2492 }
2493
2494 /* Note that we do not use cp_type_quals below; given "const
2495 int[3]", the "const" is emitted with the "int", not with the
2496 array. */
2497 cp_cv_quals quals = TYPE_QUALS (type);
2498
2499 if (quals & TYPE_QUAL_RESTRICT)
2500 {
2501 write_char ('r');
2502 ++num_qualifiers;
2503 }
2504 if (quals & TYPE_QUAL_VOLATILE)
2505 {
2506 write_char ('V');
2507 ++num_qualifiers;
2508 }
2509 if (quals & TYPE_QUAL_CONST)
2510 {
2511 write_char ('K');
2512 ++num_qualifiers;
2513 }
2514
2515 return num_qualifiers;
2516}
2517
2518/* Non-terminal <builtin-type>.
2519
2520 <builtin-type> ::= v # void
2521 ::= b # bool
2522 ::= w # wchar_t
2523 ::= c # char
2524 ::= a # signed char
2525 ::= h # unsigned char
2526 ::= s # short
2527 ::= t # unsigned short
2528 ::= i # int
2529 ::= j # unsigned int
2530 ::= l # long
2531 ::= m # unsigned long
2532 ::= x # long long, __int64
2533 ::= y # unsigned long long, __int64
2534 ::= n # __int128
2535 ::= o # unsigned __int128
2536 ::= f # float
2537 ::= d # double
2538 ::= e # long double, __float80
2539 ::= g # __float128 [not supported]
2540 ::= u <source-name> # vendor extended type */
2541
2542static void
2543write_builtin_type (tree type)
2544{
2545 if (TYPE_CANONICAL (type))
2546 type = TYPE_CANONICAL (type);
2547
2548 switch (TREE_CODE (type))
2549 {
2550 case VOID_TYPE:
2551 write_char ('v');
2552 break;
2553
2554 case BOOLEAN_TYPE:
2555 write_char ('b');
2556 break;
2557
2558 case INTEGER_TYPE:
2559 /* TYPE may still be wchar_t, char16_t, or char32_t, since that
2560 isn't in integer_type_nodes. */
2561 if (type == wchar_type_node)
2562 write_char ('w');
2563 else if (type == char16_type_node)
2564 write_string ("Ds");
2565 else if (type == char32_type_node)
2566 write_string ("Di");
2567 else
2568 {
2569 size_t itk;
2570 /* Assume TYPE is one of the shared integer type nodes. Find
2571 it in the array of these nodes. */
2572 iagain:
2573 for (itk = 0; itk < itk_none; ++itk)
2574 if (integer_types[itk] != NULL_TREE
2575 && integer_type_codes[itk] != '\0'
2576 && type == integer_types[itk])
2577 {
2578 /* Print the corresponding single-letter code. */
2579 write_char (integer_type_codes[itk]);
2580 break;
2581 }
2582
2583 if (itk == itk_none)
2584 {
2585 tree t = c_common_type_for_mode (TYPE_MODE (type),
2586 TYPE_UNSIGNED (type));
2587 if (type != t)
2588 {
2589 type = t;
2590 goto iagain;
2591 }
2592
2593 if (TYPE_PRECISION (type) == 128)
2594 write_char (TYPE_UNSIGNED (type) ? 'o' : 'n');
2595 else
2596 {
2597 /* Allow for cases where TYPE is not one of the shared
2598 integer type nodes and write a "vendor extended builtin
2599 type" with a name the form intN or uintN, respectively.
2600 Situations like this can happen if you have an
2601 __attribute__((__mode__(__SI__))) type and use exotic
2602 switches like '-mint8' on AVR. Of course, this is
2603 undefined by the C++ ABI (and '-mint8' is not even
2604 Standard C conforming), but when using such special
2605 options you're pretty much in nowhere land anyway. */
2606 const char *prefix;
2607 char prec[11]; /* up to ten digits for an unsigned */
2608
2609 prefix = TYPE_UNSIGNED (type) ? "uint" : "int";
2610 sprintf (prec, "%u", (unsigned) TYPE_PRECISION (type));
2611 write_char ('u'); /* "vendor extended builtin type" */
2612 write_unsigned_number (strlen (prefix) + strlen (prec));
2613 write_string (prefix);
2614 write_string (prec);
2615 }
2616 }
2617 }
2618 break;
2619
2620 case REAL_TYPE:
2621 if (type == float_type_node)
2622 write_char ('f');
2623 else if (type == double_type_node)
2624 write_char ('d');
2625 else if (type == long_double_type_node)
2626 write_char ('e');
2627 else if (type == dfloat32_type_node)
2628 write_string ("Df");
2629 else if (type == dfloat64_type_node)
2630 write_string ("Dd");
2631 else if (type == dfloat128_type_node)
2632 write_string ("De");
2633 else
2634 gcc_unreachable ();
2635 break;
2636
2637 case FIXED_POINT_TYPE:
2638 write_string ("DF");
2639 if (GET_MODE_IBIT (TYPE_MODE (type)) > 0)
2640 write_unsigned_number (GET_MODE_IBIT (TYPE_MODE (type)));
2641 if (type == fract_type_node
2642 || type == sat_fract_type_node
2643 || type == accum_type_node
2644 || type == sat_accum_type_node)
2645 write_char ('i');
2646 else if (type == unsigned_fract_type_node
2647 || type == sat_unsigned_fract_type_node
2648 || type == unsigned_accum_type_node
2649 || type == sat_unsigned_accum_type_node)
2650 write_char ('j');
2651 else if (type == short_fract_type_node
2652 || type == sat_short_fract_type_node
2653 || type == short_accum_type_node
2654 || type == sat_short_accum_type_node)
2655 write_char ('s');
2656 else if (type == unsigned_short_fract_type_node
2657 || type == sat_unsigned_short_fract_type_node
2658 || type == unsigned_short_accum_type_node
2659 || type == sat_unsigned_short_accum_type_node)
2660 write_char ('t');
2661 else if (type == long_fract_type_node
2662 || type == sat_long_fract_type_node
2663 || type == long_accum_type_node
2664 || type == sat_long_accum_type_node)
2665 write_char ('l');
2666 else if (type == unsigned_long_fract_type_node
2667 || type == sat_unsigned_long_fract_type_node
2668 || type == unsigned_long_accum_type_node
2669 || type == sat_unsigned_long_accum_type_node)
2670 write_char ('m');
2671 else if (type == long_long_fract_type_node
2672 || type == sat_long_long_fract_type_node
2673 || type == long_long_accum_type_node
2674 || type == sat_long_long_accum_type_node)
2675 write_char ('x');
2676 else if (type == unsigned_long_long_fract_type_node
2677 || type == sat_unsigned_long_long_fract_type_node
2678 || type == unsigned_long_long_accum_type_node
2679 || type == sat_unsigned_long_long_accum_type_node)
2680 write_char ('y');
2681 else
2682 sorry ("mangling unknown fixed point type");
2683 write_unsigned_number (GET_MODE_FBIT (TYPE_MODE (type)));
2684 if (TYPE_SATURATING (type))
2685 write_char ('s');
2686 else
2687 write_char ('n');
2688 break;
2689
2690 default:
2691 gcc_unreachable ();
2692 }
2693}
2694
2695/* Non-terminal <function-type>. NODE is a FUNCTION_TYPE or
2696 METHOD_TYPE. The return type is mangled before the parameter
2697 types.
2698
2699 <function-type> ::= F [Y] <bare-function-type> [<ref-qualifier>] E */
2700
2701static void
2702write_function_type (const tree type)
2703{
2704 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("function-type", type);
2705
2706 /* For a pointer to member function, the function type may have
2707 cv-qualifiers, indicating the quals for the artificial 'this'
2708 parameter. */
2709 if (TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
2710 {
2711 /* The first parameter must be a POINTER_TYPE pointing to the
2712 `this' parameter. */
2713 tree this_type = class_of_this_parm (type);
2714 write_CV_qualifiers_for_type (this_type);
2715 }
2716
2717 write_exception_spec (TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (type));
2718
2719 if (tx_safe_fn_type_p (type))
2720 write_string ("Dx");
2721
2722 write_char ('F');
2723 /* We don't track whether or not a type is `extern "C"'. Note that
2724 you can have an `extern "C"' function that does not have
2725 `extern "C"' type, and vice versa:
2726
2727 extern "C" typedef void function_t();
2728 function_t f; // f has C++ linkage, but its type is
2729 // `extern "C"'
2730
2731 typedef void function_t();
2732 extern "C" function_t f; // Vice versa.
2733
2734 See [dcl.link]. */
2735 write_bare_function_type (type, /*include_return_type_p=*/1,
2736 /*decl=*/NULL);
2737 if (FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED (type))
2738 {
2739 if (FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED (type))
2740 write_char ('O');
2741 else
2742 write_char ('R');
2743 }
2744 write_char ('E');
2745}
2746
2747/* Non-terminal <bare-function-type>. TYPE is a FUNCTION_TYPE or
2748 METHOD_TYPE. If INCLUDE_RETURN_TYPE is nonzero, the return value
2749 is mangled before the parameter types. If non-NULL, DECL is
2750 FUNCTION_DECL for the function whose type is being emitted. */
2751
2752static void
2753write_bare_function_type (const tree type, const int include_return_type_p,
2754 const tree decl)
2755{
2756 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("bare-function-type", type);
2757
2758 /* Mangle the return type, if requested. */
2759 if (include_return_type_p)
2760 write_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
2761
2762 /* Now mangle the types of the arguments. */
2763 ++G.parm_depth;
2764 write_method_parms (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type),
2765 TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE,
2766 decl);
2767 --G.parm_depth;
2768}
2769
2770/* Write the mangled representation of a method parameter list of
2771 types given in PARM_TYPES. If METHOD_P is nonzero, the function is
2772 considered a non-static method, and the this parameter is omitted.
2773 If non-NULL, DECL is the FUNCTION_DECL for the function whose
2774 parameters are being emitted. */
2775
2776static void
2777write_method_parms (tree parm_types, const int method_p, const tree decl)
2778{
2779 tree first_parm_type;
2780 tree parm_decl = decl ? DECL_ARGUMENTS (decl) : NULL_TREE;
2781
2782 /* Assume this parameter type list is variable-length. If it ends
2783 with a void type, then it's not. */
2784 int varargs_p = 1;
2785
2786 /* If this is a member function, skip the first arg, which is the
2787 this pointer.
2788 "Member functions do not encode the type of their implicit this
2789 parameter."
2790
2791 Similarly, there's no need to mangle artificial parameters, like
2792 the VTT parameters for constructors and destructors. */
2793 if (method_p)
2794 {
2795 parm_types = TREE_CHAIN (parm_types);
2796 parm_decl = parm_decl ? DECL_CHAIN (parm_decl) : NULL_TREE;
2797
2798 while (parm_decl && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (parm_decl))
2799 {
2800 parm_types = TREE_CHAIN (parm_types);
2801 parm_decl = DECL_CHAIN (parm_decl);
2802 }
2803
2804 if (decl && ctor_omit_inherited_parms (decl))
2805 /* Bring back parameters omitted from an inherited ctor. */
2806 parm_types = FUNCTION_FIRST_USER_PARMTYPE (DECL_ORIGIN (decl));
2807 }
2808
2809 for (first_parm_type = parm_types;
2810 parm_types;
2811 parm_types = TREE_CHAIN (parm_types))
2812 {
2813 tree parm = TREE_VALUE (parm_types);
2814 if (parm == void_type_node)
2815 {
2816 /* "Empty parameter lists, whether declared as () or
2817 conventionally as (void), are encoded with a void parameter
2818 (v)." */
2819 if (parm_types == first_parm_type)
2820 write_type (parm);
2821 /* If the parm list is terminated with a void type, it's
2822 fixed-length. */
2823 varargs_p = 0;
2824 /* A void type better be the last one. */
2825 gcc_assert (TREE_CHAIN (parm_types) == NULL);
2826 }
2827 else
2828 write_type (parm);
2829 }
2830
2831 if (varargs_p)
2832 /* <builtin-type> ::= z # ellipsis */
2833 write_char ('z');
2834}
2835
2836/* <class-enum-type> ::= <name> */
2837
2838static void
2839write_class_enum_type (const tree type)
2840{
2841 write_name (TYPE_NAME (type), /*ignore_local_scope=*/0);
2842}

2844/* Non-terminal <template-args>. ARGS is a TREE_VEC of template
2845 arguments.
2846
2847 <template-args> ::= I <template-arg>* E */
2848
2849static void
2850write_template_args (tree args)
2851{
2852 int i;
2853 int length = 0;
2854
2855 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("template-args", args);
2856
2857 write_char ('I');
2858
2859 if (args)
2860 length = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args);
2861
2862 if (args && length && TREE_CODE (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, 0)) == TREE_VEC)
2863 {
2864 /* We have nested template args. We want the innermost template
2865 argument list. */
2866 args = TREE_VEC_ELT (args, length - 1);
2867 length = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args);
2868 }
2869 for (i = 0; i < length; ++i)
2870 write_template_arg (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, i));
2871
2872 write_char ('E');
2873}
