2875/* Write out the
2876 <unqualified-name>
2877 <unqualified-name> <template-args>
2878 part of SCOPE_REF or COMPONENT_REF mangling. */
2879
2880static void
2881write_member_name (tree member)
2882{
2883 if (abi_version_at_least (11) && IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (member))
2884 {
2885 write_string ("on");
2886 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (11))
2887 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
2888 }
2889 if (identifier_p (member))
2890 write_unqualified_id (member);
2891 else if (DECL_P (member))
2892 write_unqualified_name (member);
2893 else if (TREE_CODE (member) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
2894 {
2895 tree name = TREE_OPERAND (member, 0);
2896 if (TREE_CODE (name) == OVERLOAD)
2897 name = OVL_FUNCTION (name);
2898 write_member_name (name);
2899 write_template_args (TREE_OPERAND (member, 1));
2900 }
2901 else
2902 write_expression (member);
2903}
2904
2905/* <expression> ::= <unary operator-name> <expression>
2906 ::= <binary operator-name> <expression> <expression>
2907 ::= <expr-primary>
2908
2909 <expr-primary> ::= <template-param>
2910 ::= L <type> <value number> E # literal
2911 ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
2912 ::= st <type> # sizeof
2913 ::= sr <type> <unqualified-name> # dependent name
2914 ::= sr <type> <unqualified-name> <template-args> */
2915
2916static void
2917write_expression (tree expr)
2918{
2919 enum tree_code code = TREE_CODE (expr);
2920
2921 /* Skip NOP_EXPR and CONVERT_EXPR. They can occur when (say) a pointer
2922 argument is converted (via qualification conversions) to another type. */
2923 while (CONVERT_EXPR_CODE_P (code)
2924 /* Parentheses aren't mangled. */
2925 || code == PAREN_EXPR
2926 || TREE_CODE (expr) == NON_LVALUE_EXPR)
2927 {
2928 expr = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
2929 code = TREE_CODE (expr);
2930 }
2931
2932 if (code == BASELINK
2933 && (!type_unknown_p (expr)
2934 || !BASELINK_QUALIFIED_P (expr)))
2935 {
2936 expr = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (expr);
2937 code = TREE_CODE (expr);
2938 }
2939
2940 /* Handle pointers-to-members by making them look like expression
2941 nodes. */
2942 if (code == PTRMEM_CST)
2943 {
2944 expr = build_nt (ADDR_EXPR,
2945 build_qualified_name (/*type=*/NULL_TREE,
2946 PTRMEM_CST_CLASS (expr),
2947 PTRMEM_CST_MEMBER (expr),
2948 /*template_p=*/false));
2949 code = TREE_CODE (expr);
2950 }
2951
2952 /* Handle template parameters. */
2953 if (code == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM
2954 || code == TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM
2955 || code == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM
2956 || code == TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX)
2957 write_template_param (expr);
2958 /* Handle literals. */
2959 else if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (code) == tcc_constant
2960 || code == CONST_DECL)
2961 write_template_arg_literal (expr);
2962 else if (code == PARM_DECL && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (expr))
2963 {
2964 gcc_assert (!strcmp ("this", IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (expr))));
2965 write_string ("fpT");
2966 }
2967 else if (code == PARM_DECL)
2968 {
2969 /* A function parameter used in a late-specified return type. */
2970 int index = DECL_PARM_INDEX (expr);
2971 int level = DECL_PARM_LEVEL (expr);
2972 int delta = G.parm_depth - level + 1;
2973 gcc_assert (index >= 1);
2974 write_char ('f');
2975 if (delta != 0)
2976 {
2977 if (abi_version_at_least (5))
2978 {
2979 /* Let L be the number of function prototype scopes from the
2980 innermost one (in which the parameter reference occurs) up
2981 to (and including) the one containing the declaration of
2982 the referenced parameter. If the parameter declaration
2983 clause of the innermost function prototype scope has been
2984 completely seen, it is not counted (in that case -- which
2985 is perhaps the most common -- L can be zero). */
2986 write_char ('L');
2987 write_unsigned_number (delta - 1);
2988 }
2989 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (5))
2990 G.need_abi_warning = true;
2991 }
2992 write_char ('p');
2993 write_compact_number (index - 1);
2994 }
2995 else if (DECL_P (expr))
2996 {
2997 write_char ('L');
2998 write_mangled_name (expr, false);
2999 write_char ('E');
3000 }
3001 else if (TREE_CODE (expr) == SIZEOF_EXPR)
3002 {
3003 tree op = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3004
3005 if (PACK_EXPANSION_P (op))
3006 {
3007 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (11))
3008 G.need_abi_warning = true;
3009 if (abi_version_at_least (11))
3010 {
3011 /* sZ rather than szDp. */
3012 write_string ("sZ");
3013 write_expression (PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN (op));
3014 return;
3015 }
3016 }
3017
3018 if (SIZEOF_EXPR_TYPE_P (expr))
3019 {
3020 write_string ("st");
3021 write_type (TREE_TYPE (op));
3022 }
3023 else if (ARGUMENT_PACK_P (op))
3024 {
3025 tree args = ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS (op);
3026 int length = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args);
3027 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (10))
3028 G.need_abi_warning = true;
3029 if (abi_version_at_least (10))
3030 {
3031 /* sP <template-arg>* E # sizeof...(T), size of a captured
3032 template parameter pack from an alias template */
3033 write_string ("sP");
3034 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i)
3035 write_template_arg (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, i));
3036 write_char ('E');
3037 }
3038 else
3039 {
3040 /* In GCC 5 we represented this sizeof wrong, with the effect
3041 that we mangled it as the last element of the pack. */
3042 tree arg = TREE_VEC_ELT (args, length-1);
3043 if (TYPE_P (op))
3044 {
3045 write_string ("st");
3046 write_type (arg);
3047 }
3048 else
3049 {
3050 write_string ("sz");
3051 write_expression (arg);
3052 }
3053 }
3054 }
3055 else if (TYPE_P (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)))
3056 {
3057 write_string ("st");
3058 write_type (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0));
3059 }
3060 else
3061 goto normal_expr;
3062 }
3063 else if (TREE_CODE (expr) == ALIGNOF_EXPR
3064 && TYPE_P (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)))
3065 {
3066 write_string ("at");
3067 write_type (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0));
3068 }
3069 else if (code == SCOPE_REF
3070 || code == BASELINK)
3071 {
3072 tree scope, member;
3073 if (code == SCOPE_REF)
3074 {
3075 scope = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3076 member = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 1);
3077 }
3078 else
3079 {
3080 scope = BINFO_TYPE (BASELINK_ACCESS_BINFO (expr));
3081 member = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (expr);
3082 }
3083
3084 /* If the MEMBER is a real declaration, then the qualifying
3085 scope was not dependent. Ideally, we would not have a
3086 SCOPE_REF in those cases, but sometimes we do. If the second
3087 argument is a DECL, then the name must not have been
3088 dependent. */
3089 if (DECL_P (member))
3090 write_expression (member);
3091 else
3092 {
3093 write_string ("sr");
3094 write_type (scope);
3095 write_member_name (member);
3096 }
3097 }
3098 else if (INDIRECT_REF_P (expr)
3099 && TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0))
3100 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0))) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
3101 {
3102 write_expression (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0));
3103 }
3104 else if (identifier_p (expr))
3105 {
3106 /* An operator name appearing as a dependent name needs to be
3107 specially marked to disambiguate between a use of the operator
3108 name and a use of the operator in an expression. */
3109 if (IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (expr))
3110 write_string ("on");
3111 write_unqualified_id (expr);
3112 }
3113 else if (TREE_CODE (expr) == TEMPLATE_ID_EXPR)
3114 {
3115 tree fn = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3116 if (is_overloaded_fn (fn))
3117 fn = get_first_fn (fn);
3118 if (DECL_P (fn))
3119 fn = DECL_NAME (fn);
3120 if (IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (fn))
3121 write_string ("on");
3122 write_unqualified_id (fn);
3123 write_template_args (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 1));
3124 }
3125 else if (TREE_CODE (expr) == MODOP_EXPR)
3126 {
3127 enum tree_code subop = TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 1));
3128 const char *name = (assignment_operator_name_info[(int) subop]
3129 .mangled_name);
3130 write_string (name);
3131 write_expression (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0));
3132 write_expression (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 2));
3133 }
3134 else if (code == NEW_EXPR || code == VEC_NEW_EXPR)
3135 {
3136 /* ::= [gs] nw <expression>* _ <type> E
3137 ::= [gs] nw <expression>* _ <type> <initializer>
3138 ::= [gs] na <expression>* _ <type> E
3139 ::= [gs] na <expression>* _ <type> <initializer>
3140 <initializer> ::= pi <expression>* E */
3141 tree placement = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3142 tree type = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 1);
3143 tree nelts = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 2);
3144 tree init = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 3);
3145 tree t;
3146
3147 gcc_assert (code == NEW_EXPR);
3148 if (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 2))
3149 code = VEC_NEW_EXPR;
3150
3151 if (NEW_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL (expr))
3152 write_string ("gs");
3153
3154 write_string (operator_name_info[(int) code].mangled_name);
3155
3156 for (t = placement; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
3157 write_expression (TREE_VALUE (t));
3158
3159 write_char ('_');
3160
3161 if (nelts)
3162 {
3163 tree domain;
3164 ++processing_template_decl;
3165 domain = compute_array_index_type (NULL_TREE, nelts,
3166 tf_warning_or_error);
3167 type = build_cplus_array_type (type, domain);
3168 --processing_template_decl;
3169 }
3170 write_type (type);
3171
3172 if (init && TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST
3173 && DIRECT_LIST_INIT_P (TREE_VALUE (init)))
3174 write_expression (TREE_VALUE (init));
3175 else
3176 {
3177 if (init)
3178 write_string ("pi");
3179 if (init && init != void_node)
3180 for (t = init; t; t = TREE_CHAIN (t))
3181 write_expression (TREE_VALUE (t));
3182 write_char ('E');
3183 }
3184 }
3185 else if (code == DELETE_EXPR || code == VEC_DELETE_EXPR)
3186 {
3187 gcc_assert (code == DELETE_EXPR);
3188 if (DELETE_EXPR_USE_VEC (expr))
3189 code = VEC_DELETE_EXPR;
3190
3191 if (DELETE_EXPR_USE_GLOBAL (expr))
3192 write_string ("gs");
3193
3194 write_string (operator_name_info[(int) code].mangled_name);
3195
3196 write_expression (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0));
3197 }
3198 else if (code == THROW_EXPR)
3199 {
3200 tree op = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3201 if (op)
3202 {
3203 write_string ("tw");
3204 write_expression (op);
3205 }
3206 else
3207 write_string ("tr");
3208 }
3209 else if (code == CONSTRUCTOR)
3210 {
3211 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *elts = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (expr);
3212 unsigned i; tree val;
3213
3214 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (expr))
3215 write_string ("il");
3216 else
3217 {
3218 write_string ("tl");
3219 write_type (TREE_TYPE (expr));
3220 }
3221 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_VALUE (elts, i, val)
3222 write_expression (val);
3223 write_char ('E');
3224 }
3225 else if (dependent_name (expr))
3226 {
3227 write_unqualified_id (dependent_name (expr));
3228 }
3229 else
3230 {
3231 normal_expr:
3232 int i, len;
3233 const char *name;
3234
3235 /* When we bind a variable or function to a non-type template
3236 argument with reference type, we create an ADDR_EXPR to show
3237 the fact that the entity's address has been taken. But, we
3238 don't actually want to output a mangling code for the `&'. */
3239 if (TREE_CODE (expr) == ADDR_EXPR
3240 && TREE_TYPE (expr)
3241 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (expr)) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
3242 {
3243 expr = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3244 if (DECL_P (expr))
3245 {
3246 write_expression (expr);
3247 return;
3248 }
3249
3250 code = TREE_CODE (expr);
3251 }
3252
3253 if (code == COMPONENT_REF)
3254 {
3255 tree ob = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3256
3257 if (TREE_CODE (ob) == ARROW_EXPR)
3258 {
3259 write_string (operator_name_info[(int)code].mangled_name);
3260 ob = TREE_OPERAND (ob, 0);
3261 write_expression (ob);
3262 }
3263 else if (!is_dummy_object (ob))
3264 {
3265 write_string ("dt");
3266 write_expression (ob);
3267 }
3268 /* else, for a non-static data member with no associated object (in
3269 unevaluated context), use the unresolved-name mangling. */
3270
3271 write_member_name (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 1));
3272 return;
3273 }
3274
3275 /* If it wasn't any of those, recursively expand the expression. */
3276 name = operator_name_info[(int) code].mangled_name;
3277
3278 /* We used to mangle const_cast and static_cast like a C cast. */
3279 if (code == CONST_CAST_EXPR
3280 || code == STATIC_CAST_EXPR)
3281 {
3282 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (6))
3283 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
3284 if (!abi_version_at_least (6))
3285 name = operator_name_info[CAST_EXPR].mangled_name;
3286 }
3287
3288 if (name == NULL)
3289 {
3290 switch (code)
3291 {
3292 case TRAIT_EXPR:
3293 error ("use of built-in trait %qE in function signature; "
3294 "use library traits instead", expr);
3295 break;
3296
3297 default:
3298 sorry ("mangling %C", code);
3299 break;
3300 }
3301 return;
3302 }
3303 else
3304 write_string (name);
3305
3306 switch (code)
3307 {
3308 case CALL_EXPR:
3309 {
3310 tree fn = CALL_EXPR_FN (expr);
3311
3312 if (TREE_CODE (fn) == ADDR_EXPR)
3313 fn = TREE_OPERAND (fn, 0);
3314
3315 /* Mangle a dependent name as the name, not whatever happens to
3316 be the first function in the overload set. */
3317 if ((TREE_CODE (fn) == FUNCTION_DECL
3318 || TREE_CODE (fn) == OVERLOAD)
3319 && type_dependent_expression_p_push (expr))
3320 fn = DECL_NAME (get_first_fn (fn));
3321
3322 write_expression (fn);
3323 }
3324
3325 for (i = 0; i < call_expr_nargs (expr); ++i)
3326 write_expression (CALL_EXPR_ARG (expr, i));
3327 write_char ('E');
3328 break;
3329
3330 case CAST_EXPR:
3331 write_type (TREE_TYPE (expr));
3332 if (list_length (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)) == 1)
3333 write_expression (TREE_VALUE (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0)));
3334 else
3335 {
3336 tree args = TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0);
3337 write_char ('_');
3338 for (; args; args = TREE_CHAIN (args))
3339 write_expression (TREE_VALUE (args));
3340 write_char ('E');
3341 }
3342 break;
3343
3344 case DYNAMIC_CAST_EXPR:
3345 case REINTERPRET_CAST_EXPR:
3346 case STATIC_CAST_EXPR:
3347 case CONST_CAST_EXPR:
3348 write_type (TREE_TYPE (expr));
3349 write_expression (TREE_OPERAND (expr, 0));
3350 break;
3351
3352 case PREINCREMENT_EXPR:
3353 case PREDECREMENT_EXPR:
3354 if (abi_version_at_least (6))
3355 write_char ('_');
3356 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (6))
3357 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
3358 /* Fall through. */
3359
3360 default:
3361 /* In the middle-end, some expressions have more operands than
3362 they do in templates (and mangling). */
3363 len = cp_tree_operand_length (expr);
3364
3365 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
3366 {
3367 tree operand = TREE_OPERAND (expr, i);
3368 /* As a GNU extension, the middle operand of a
3369 conditional may be omitted. Since expression
3370 manglings are supposed to represent the input token
3371 stream, there's no good way to mangle such an
3372 expression without extending the C++ ABI. */
3373 if (code == COND_EXPR && i == 1 && !operand)
3374 {
3375 error ("omitted middle operand to %<?:%> operand "
3376 "cannot be mangled");
3377 continue;
3378 }
3379 else if (FOLD_EXPR_P (expr))
3380 {
3381 /* The first 'operand' of a fold-expression is the operator
3382 that it folds over. */
3383 if (i == 0)
3384 {
3385 int fcode = TREE_INT_CST_LOW (operand);
3386 write_string (operator_name_info[fcode].mangled_name);
3387 continue;
3388 }
3389 else if (code == BINARY_LEFT_FOLD_EXPR)
3390 {
3391 /* The order of operands of the binary left and right
3392 folds is the same, but we want to mangle them in
3393 lexical order, i.e. non-pack first. */
3394 if (i == 1)
3395 operand = FOLD_EXPR_INIT (expr);
3396 else
3397 operand = FOLD_EXPR_PACK (expr);
3398 }
3399 if (PACK_EXPANSION_P (operand))
3400 operand = PACK_EXPANSION_PATTERN (operand);
3401 }
3402 write_expression (operand);
3403 }
3404 }
3405 }
3406}
3407
3408/* Literal subcase of non-terminal <template-arg>.
3409
3410 "Literal arguments, e.g. "A<42L>", are encoded with their type
3411 and value. Negative integer values are preceded with "n"; for
3412 example, "A<-42L>" becomes "1AILln42EE". The bool value false is
3413 encoded as 0, true as 1." */
3414
3415static void
3416write_template_arg_literal (const tree value)
3417{
3418 write_char ('L');
3419 write_type (TREE_TYPE (value));
3420
3421 /* Write a null member pointer value as (type)0, regardless of its
3422 real representation. */
3423 if (null_member_pointer_value_p (value))
3424 write_integer_cst (integer_zero_node);
3425 else
3426 switch (TREE_CODE (value))
3427 {
3428 case CONST_DECL:
3429 write_integer_cst (DECL_INITIAL (value));
3430 break;
3431
3432 case INTEGER_CST:
3433 gcc_assert (!same_type_p (TREE_TYPE (value), boolean_type_node)
3434 || integer_zerop (value) || integer_onep (value));
3435 write_integer_cst (value);
3436 break;
3437
3438 case REAL_CST:
3439 write_real_cst (value);
3440 break;
3441
3442 case COMPLEX_CST:
3443 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_REALPART (value)) == INTEGER_CST
3444 && TREE_CODE (TREE_IMAGPART (value)) == INTEGER_CST)
3445 {
3446 write_integer_cst (TREE_REALPART (value));
3447 write_char ('_');
3448 write_integer_cst (TREE_IMAGPART (value));
3449 }
3450 else if (TREE_CODE (TREE_REALPART (value)) == REAL_CST
3451 && TREE_CODE (TREE_IMAGPART (value)) == REAL_CST)
3452 {
3453 write_real_cst (TREE_REALPART (value));
3454 write_char ('_');
3455 write_real_cst (TREE_IMAGPART (value));
3456 }
3457 else
3458 gcc_unreachable ();
3459 break;
3460
3461 case STRING_CST:
3462 sorry ("string literal in function template signature");
3463 break;
3464
3465 default:
3466 gcc_unreachable ();
3467 }
3468
3469 write_char ('E');
3470}
3471
3472/* Non-terminal <template-arg>.
3473
3474 <template-arg> ::= <type> # type
3475 ::= L <type> </value/ number> E # literal
3476 ::= LZ <name> E # external name
3477 ::= X <expression> E # expression */
3478
3479static void
3480write_template_arg (tree node)
3481{
3482 enum tree_code code = TREE_CODE (node);
3483
3484 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("template-arg", node);
3485
3486 /* A template template parameter's argument list contains TREE_LIST
3487 nodes of which the value field is the actual argument. */
3488 if (code == TREE_LIST)
3489 {
3490 node = TREE_VALUE (node);
3491 /* If it's a decl, deal with its type instead. */
3492 if (DECL_P (node))
3493 {
3494 node = TREE_TYPE (node);
3495 code = TREE_CODE (node);
3496 }
3497 }
3498
3499 if (REFERENCE_REF_P (node))
3500 node = TREE_OPERAND (node, 0);
3501 if (TREE_CODE (node) == NOP_EXPR
3502 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (node)) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
3503 {
3504 /* Template parameters can be of reference type. To maintain
3505 internal consistency, such arguments use a conversion from
3506 address of object to reference type. */
3507 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (node, 0)) == ADDR_EXPR);
3508 node = TREE_OPERAND (TREE_OPERAND (node, 0), 0);
3509 }
3510
3511 if (TREE_CODE (node) == BASELINK
3512 && !type_unknown_p (node))
3513 {
3514 if (abi_version_at_least (6))
3515 node = BASELINK_FUNCTIONS (node);
3516 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (6))
3517 /* We wrongly wrapped a class-scope function in X/E. */
3518 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
3519 }
3520
3521 if (ARGUMENT_PACK_P (node))
3522 {
3523 /* Expand the template argument pack. */
3524 tree args = ARGUMENT_PACK_ARGS (node);
3525 int i, length = TREE_VEC_LENGTH (args);
3526 if (abi_version_at_least (6))
3527 write_char ('J');
3528 else
3529 write_char ('I');
3530 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (6))
3531 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
3532 for (i = 0; i < length; ++i)
3533 write_template_arg (TREE_VEC_ELT (args, i));
3534 write_char ('E');
3535 }
3536 else if (TYPE_P (node))
3537 write_type (node);
3538 else if (code == TEMPLATE_DECL)
3539 /* A template appearing as a template arg is a template template arg. */
3540 write_template_template_arg (node);
3541 else if ((TREE_CODE_CLASS (code) == tcc_constant && code != PTRMEM_CST)
3542 || code == CONST_DECL
3543 || null_member_pointer_value_p (node))
3544 write_template_arg_literal (node);
3545 else if (DECL_P (node))
3546 {
3547 write_char ('L');
3548 /* Until ABI version 3, the underscore before the mangled name
3549 was incorrectly omitted. */
3550 if (!abi_version_at_least (3))
3551 write_char ('Z');
3552 else
3553 write_string ("_Z");
3554 if (abi_warn_or_compat_version_crosses (3))
3555 G.need_abi_warning = 1;
3556 write_encoding (node);
3557 write_char ('E');
3558 }
3559 else
3560 {
3561 /* Template arguments may be expressions. */
3562 write_char ('X');
3563 write_expression (node);
3564 write_char ('E');
3565 }
3566}
3567
3568/* <template-template-arg>
3569 ::= <name>
3570 ::= <substitution> */
3571
3572static void
3573write_template_template_arg (const tree decl)
3574{
3575 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("template-template-arg", decl);
3576
3577 if (find_substitution (decl))
3578 return;
3579 write_name (decl, /*ignore_local_scope=*/0);
3580 add_substitution (decl);
3581}
3582
3583
3584/* Non-terminal <array-type>. TYPE is an ARRAY_TYPE.
3585
3586 <array-type> ::= A [</dimension/ number>] _ </element/ type>
3587 ::= A <expression> _ </element/ type>
3588
3589 "Array types encode the dimension (number of elements) and the
3590 element type. For variable length arrays, the dimension (but not
3591 the '_' separator) is omitted."
3592 Note that for flexible array members, like for other arrays of
3593 unspecified size, the dimension is also omitted. */
3594
3595static void
3596write_array_type (const tree type)
3597{
3598 write_char ('A');
3599 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
3600 {
3601 tree index_type;
3602
3603 index_type = TYPE_DOMAIN (type);
3604 /* The INDEX_TYPE gives the upper and lower bounds of the array.
3605 It's null for flexible array members which have no upper bound
3606 (this is a change from GCC 5 and prior where such members were
3607 incorrectly mangled as zero-length arrays). */
3608 if (tree max = TYPE_MAX_VALUE (index_type))
3609 {
3610 if (TREE_CODE (max) == INTEGER_CST)
3611 {
3612 /* The ABI specifies that we should mangle the number of
3613 elements in the array, not the largest allowed index. */
3614 offset_int wmax = wi::to_offset (max) + 1;
3615 /* Truncate the result - this will mangle [0, SIZE_INT_MAX]
3616 number of elements as zero. */
3617 wmax = wi::zext (wmax, TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (max)));
3618 gcc_assert (wi::fits_uhwi_p (wmax));
3619 write_unsigned_number (wmax.to_uhwi ());
3620 }
3621 else
3622 {
3623 max = TREE_OPERAND (max, 0);
3624 write_expression (max);
3625 }
3626 }
3627 }
3628 write_char ('_');
3629 write_type (TREE_TYPE (type));
3630}
3631
3632/* Non-terminal <pointer-to-member-type> for pointer-to-member
3633 variables. TYPE is a pointer-to-member POINTER_TYPE.
3634
3635 <pointer-to-member-type> ::= M </class/ type> </member/ type> */
3636
3637static void
3638write_pointer_to_member_type (const tree type)
3639{
3640 write_char ('M');
3641 write_type (TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (type));
3642 write_type (TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (type));
3643}
3644
3645/* Non-terminal <template-param>. PARM is a TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM,
3646 TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM, BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM or a
3647 TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX.
3648
3649 <template-param> ::= T </parameter/ number> _ */
3650
3651static void
3652write_template_param (const tree parm)
3653{
3654 int parm_index;
3655
3656 MANGLE_TRACE_TREE ("template-parm", parm);
3657
3658 switch (TREE_CODE (parm))
3659 {
3660 case TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM:
3661 case TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM:
3662 case BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM:
3663 parm_index = TEMPLATE_TYPE_IDX (parm);
3664 break;
3665
3666 case TEMPLATE_PARM_INDEX:
3667 parm_index = TEMPLATE_PARM_IDX (parm);
3668 break;
3669
3670 default:
3671 gcc_unreachable ();
3672 }
3673
3674 write_char ('T');
3675 /* NUMBER as it appears in the mangling is (-1)-indexed, with the
3676 earliest template param denoted by `_'. */
3677 write_compact_number (parm_index);
3678}
3679
3680/* <template-template-param>
3681 ::= <template-param>
3682 ::= <substitution> */
3683
3684static void
3685write_template_template_param (const tree parm)
3686{
3687 tree templ = NULL_TREE;
3688
3689 /* PARM, a TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM, is an instantiation of the
3690 template template parameter. The substitution candidate here is
3691 only the template. */
3692 if (TREE_CODE (parm) == BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM)
3693 {
3694 templ
3695 = TI_TEMPLATE (TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM_TEMPLATE_INFO (parm));
3696 if (find_substitution (templ))
3697 return;
3698 }
3699
3700 /* <template-param> encodes only the template parameter position,
3701 not its template arguments, which is fine here. */
3702 write_template_param (parm);
3703 if (templ)
3704 add_substitution (templ);
3705}
3706
3707/* Non-terminal <substitution>.
3708
3709 <substitution> ::= S <seq-id> _
3710 ::= S_ */
3711
3712static void
3713write_substitution (const int seq_id)
3714{
3715 MANGLE_TRACE ("substitution", "");
3716
3717 write_char ('S');
3718 if (seq_id > 0)
3719 write_number (seq_id - 1, /*unsigned=*/1, 36);
3720 write_char ('_');
3721}
3722
3723/* Start mangling ENTITY. */
3724
3725static inline void
3726start_mangling (const tree entity)
3727{
3728 G.entity = entity;
3729 G.need_abi_warning = false;
3730 G.need_cxx1z_warning = false;
3731 obstack_free (&name_obstack, name_base);
3732 mangle_obstack = &name_obstack;
3733 name_base = obstack_alloc (&name_obstack, 0);
3734}
3735
3736/* Done with mangling. If WARN is true, and the name of G.entity will
3737 be mangled differently in a future version of the ABI, issue a
3738 warning. */
3739
3740static void
3741finish_mangling_internal (void)
3742{
3743 /* Clear all the substitutions. */
3744 vec_safe_truncate (G.substitutions, 0);
3745
3746 /* Null-terminate the string. */
3747 write_char ('\0');
3748}
3749
3750
3751/* Like finish_mangling_internal, but return the mangled string. */
3752
3753static inline const char *
3754finish_mangling (void)
3755{
3756 finish_mangling_internal ();
3757 return (const char *) obstack_finish (mangle_obstack);
3758}
3759
3760/* Like finish_mangling_internal, but return an identifier. */
3761
3762static tree
3763finish_mangling_get_identifier (void)
3764{
3765 finish_mangling_internal ();
3766 /* Don't obstack_finish here, and the next start_mangling will
3767 remove the identifier. */
3768 return get_identifier ((const char *) obstack_base (mangle_obstack));
3769}

3771/* Initialize data structures for mangling. */
3772
3773void
3774init_mangle (void)
3775{
3776 gcc_obstack_init (&name_obstack);
3777 name_base = obstack_alloc (&name_obstack, 0);
3778 vec_alloc (G.substitutions, 0);
3779
3780 /* Cache these identifiers for quick comparison when checking for
3781 standard substitutions. */
3782 subst_identifiers[SUBID_ALLOCATOR] = get_identifier ("allocator");
3783 subst_identifiers[SUBID_BASIC_STRING] = get_identifier ("basic_string");
3784 subst_identifiers[SUBID_CHAR_TRAITS] = get_identifier ("char_traits");
3785 subst_identifiers[SUBID_BASIC_ISTREAM] = get_identifier ("basic_istream");
3786 subst_identifiers[SUBID_BASIC_OSTREAM] = get_identifier ("basic_ostream");
3787 subst_identifiers[SUBID_BASIC_IOSTREAM] = get_identifier ("basic_iostream");
3788}

3790/* Generate the mangled name of DECL. */
3791
3792static tree
3793mangle_decl_string (const tree decl)
3794{
3795 tree result;
3796 location_t saved_loc = input_location;
3797 tree saved_fn = NULL_TREE;
3798 bool template_p = false;
3799
3800 /* We shouldn't be trying to mangle an uninstantiated template. */
3801 gcc_assert (!type_dependent_expression_p (decl));
3802
3803 if (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (decl))
3804 {
3805 struct tinst_level *tl = current_instantiation ();
3806 if ((!tl || tl->decl != decl)
3807 && push_tinst_level (decl))
3808 {
3809 template_p = true;
3810 saved_fn = current_function_decl;
3811 current_function_decl = NULL_TREE;
3812 }
3813 }
3814 input_location = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl);
3815
3816 start_mangling (decl);
3817
3818 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
3819 write_type (TREE_TYPE (decl));
3820 else
3821 write_mangled_name (decl, true);
3822
3823 result = finish_mangling_get_identifier ();
3824 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
3825 fprintf (stderr, "mangle_decl_string = '%s'\n\n",
3826 IDENTIFIER_POINTER (result));
3827
3828 if (template_p)
3829 {
3830 pop_tinst_level ();
3831 current_function_decl = saved_fn;
3832 }
3833 input_location = saved_loc;
3834
3835 return result;
3836}

3838/* Return an identifier for the external mangled name of DECL. */
3839
3840static tree
3841get_mangled_id (tree decl)
3842{
3843 tree id = mangle_decl_string (decl);
3844 return targetm.mangle_decl_assembler_name (decl, id);
3845}

3847/* If DECL is an implicit mangling alias, return its symtab node; otherwise
3848 return NULL. */
3849
3850static symtab_node *
3851decl_implicit_alias_p (tree decl)
3852{
3853 if (DECL_P (decl) && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl)
3854 && DECL_IGNORED_P (decl)
3855 && (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
3856 || (VAR_P (decl) && TREE_STATIC (decl))))
3857 {
3858 symtab_node *n = symtab_node::get (decl);
3859 if (n && n->cpp_implicit_alias)
3860 return n;
3861 }
3862 return NULL;
3863}
3864
3865/* If DECL is a mangling alias, remove it from the symbol table and return
3866 true; otherwise return false. */
3867
3868bool
3869maybe_remove_implicit_alias (tree decl)
3870{
3871 if (symtab_node *n = decl_implicit_alias_p (decl))
3872 {
3873 n->remove();
3874 return true;
3875 }
3876 return false;
3877}
3878
3879/* Create an identifier for the external mangled name of DECL. */
3880
3881void
3882mangle_decl (const tree decl)
3883{
3884 tree id;
3885 bool dep;
3886
3887 /* Don't bother mangling uninstantiated templates. */
3888 ++processing_template_decl;
3889 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL)
3890 dep = dependent_type_p (TREE_TYPE (decl));
3891 else
3892 dep = (DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (decl) && DECL_TEMPLATE_INFO (decl)
3893 && any_dependent_template_arguments_p (DECL_TI_ARGS (decl)));
3894 --processing_template_decl;
3895 if (dep)
3896 return;
3897
3898 /* During LTO we keep mangled names of TYPE_DECLs for ODR type merging.
3899 It is not needed to assign names to anonymous namespace, but we use the
3900 "<anon>" marker to be able to tell if type is C++ ODR type or type
3901 produced by other language. */
3902 if (TREE_CODE (decl) == TYPE_DECL
3903 && TYPE_STUB_DECL (TREE_TYPE (decl))
3904 && !TREE_PUBLIC (TYPE_STUB_DECL (TREE_TYPE (decl))))
3905 id = get_identifier ("<anon>");
3906 else
3907 {
3908 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) != TYPE_DECL
3909 || !no_linkage_check (TREE_TYPE (decl), true));
3910 if (abi_version_at_least (10))
3911 if (tree fn = decl_function_context (decl))
3912 maybe_check_abi_tags (fn, decl);
3913 id = get_mangled_id (decl);
3914 }
3915 SET_DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (decl, id);
3916
3917 if (G.need_cxx1z_warning
3918 && (TREE_PUBLIC (decl) || DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl)))
3919 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), OPT_Wnoexcept_type,
3920 "mangled name for %qD will change in C++17 because the "
3921 "exception specification is part of a function type",
3922 decl);
3923
3924 if (id != DECL_NAME (decl)
3925 /* Don't do this for a fake symbol we aren't going to emit anyway. */
3926 && TREE_CODE (decl) != TYPE_DECL
3927 && !DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_CONSTRUCTOR_P (decl)
3928 && !DECL_MAYBE_IN_CHARGE_DESTRUCTOR_P (decl))
3929 {
3930 int save_ver = flag_abi_version;
3931 tree id2 = NULL_TREE;
3932
3933 if (!DECL_REALLY_EXTERN (decl))
3934 {
3935 bool set = false;
3936
3937 /* Check IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE before setting to avoid redundant
3938 errors from multiple definitions. */
3939 tree d = IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (id);
3940 if (!d || decl_implicit_alias_p (d))
3941 {
3942 set = true;
3943 SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (id, decl);
3944 }
3945
3946 if (!G.need_abi_warning)
3947 return;
3948
3949 /* If the mangling will change in the future, emit an alias with the
3950 future mangled name for forward-compatibility. */
3951 if (!set)
3952 {
3953 SET_IDENTIFIER_GLOBAL_VALUE (id, decl);
3954 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl), "a later -fabi-version= (or "
3955 "=0) avoids this error with a change in mangling");
3956 }
3957
3958 flag_abi_version = flag_abi_compat_version;
3959 id2 = mangle_decl_string (decl);
3960 id2 = targetm.mangle_decl_assembler_name (decl, id2);
3961 flag_abi_version = save_ver;
3962
3963 if (id2 != id)
3964 note_mangling_alias (decl, id2);
3965 }
3966
3967 if (warn_abi)
3968 {
3969 if (flag_abi_compat_version != warn_abi_version
3970 || id2 == NULL_TREE)
3971 {
3972 flag_abi_version = warn_abi_version;
3973 id2 = mangle_decl_string (decl);
3974 id2 = targetm.mangle_decl_assembler_name (decl, id2);
3975 }
3976 flag_abi_version = save_ver;
3977
3978 if (id2 == id)
3979 /* OK. */;
3980 else if (warn_abi_version != 0
3981 && abi_version_at_least (warn_abi_version))
3982 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (G.entity), OPT_Wabi,
3983 "the mangled name of %qD changed between "
3984 "-fabi-version=%d (%D) and -fabi-version=%d (%D)",
3985 G.entity, warn_abi_version, id2,
3986 save_ver, id);
3987 else
3988 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (G.entity), OPT_Wabi,
3989 "the mangled name of %qD changes between "
3990 "-fabi-version=%d (%D) and -fabi-version=%d (%D)",
3991 G.entity, save_ver, id,
3992 warn_abi_version, id2);
3993 }
3994
3995 flag_abi_version = save_ver;
3996 }
3997}

4076/* Returns an identifier for the mangled name of the decomposition
4077 artificial variable DECL. DECLS is the vector of the VAR_DECLs
4078 for the identifier-list. */
4079
4080tree
4081mangle_decomp (const tree decl, vec<tree> &decls)
4082{
4083 gcc_assert (!type_dependent_expression_p (decl));
4084
4085 location_t saved_loc = input_location;
4086 input_location = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl);
4087
4088 start_mangling (decl);
4089 write_string ("_Z");
4090
4091 tree context = decl_mangling_context (decl);
4092 gcc_assert (context != NULL_TREE);
4093
4094 bool nested = false;
4095 if (DECL_NAMESPACE_STD_P (context))
4096 write_string ("St");
4097 else if (context != global_namespace)
4098 {
4099 nested = true;
4100 write_char ('N');
4101 write_prefix (decl_mangling_context (decl));
4102 }
4103
4104 write_string ("DC");
4105 unsigned int i;
4106 tree d;
4107 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (decls, i, d)
4108 write_unqualified_name (d);
4109 write_char ('E');
4110
4111 if (nested)
4112 write_char ('E');
4113
4114 tree id = finish_mangling_get_identifier ();
4115 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
4116 fprintf (stderr, "mangle_decomp = '%s'\n\n",
4117 IDENTIFIER_POINTER (id));
4118
4119 input_location = saved_loc;
4120 return id;
4121}
4122
4123/* Return an identifier for a construction vtable group. TYPE is
4124 the most derived class in the hierarchy; BINFO is the base
4125 subobject for which this construction vtable group will be used.
4126
4127 This mangling isn't part of the ABI specification; in the ABI
4128 specification, the vtable group is dumped in the same COMDAT as the
4129 main vtable, and is referenced only from that vtable, so it doesn't
4130 need an external name. For binary formats without COMDAT sections,
4131 though, we need external names for the vtable groups.
4132
4133 We use the production
4134
4135 <special-name> ::= CT <type> <offset number> _ <base type> */
4136
4137tree
4138mangle_ctor_vtbl_for_type (const tree type, const tree binfo)
4139{
4140 tree result;
4141
4142 start_mangling (type);
4143
4144 write_string ("_Z");
4145 write_string ("TC");
4146 write_type (type);
4147 write_integer_cst (BINFO_OFFSET (binfo));
4148 write_char ('_');
4149 write_type (BINFO_TYPE (binfo));
4150
4151 result = finish_mangling_get_identifier ();
4152 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
4153 fprintf (stderr, "mangle_ctor_vtbl_for_type = %s\n\n",
4154 IDENTIFIER_POINTER (result));
4155 return result;
4156}
4157
4158/* Mangle a this pointer or result pointer adjustment.
4159
4160 <call-offset> ::= h <fixed offset number> _
4161 ::= v <fixed offset number> _ <virtual offset number> _ */
4162
4163static void
4164mangle_call_offset (const tree fixed_offset, const tree virtual_offset)
4165{
4166 write_char (virtual_offset ? 'v' : 'h');
4167
4168 /* For either flavor, write the fixed offset. */
4169 write_integer_cst (fixed_offset);
4170 write_char ('_');
4171
4172 /* For a virtual thunk, add the virtual offset. */
4173 if (virtual_offset)
4174 {
4175 write_integer_cst (virtual_offset);
4176 write_char ('_');
4177 }
4178}
4179
4180/* Return an identifier for the mangled name of a this-adjusting or
4181 covariant thunk to FN_DECL. FIXED_OFFSET is the initial adjustment
4182 to this used to find the vptr. If VIRTUAL_OFFSET is non-NULL, this
4183 is a virtual thunk, and it is the vtbl offset in
4184 bytes. THIS_ADJUSTING is nonzero for a this adjusting thunk and
4185 zero for a covariant thunk. Note, that FN_DECL might be a covariant
4186 thunk itself. A covariant thunk name always includes the adjustment
4187 for the this pointer, even if there is none.
4188
4189 <special-name> ::= T <call-offset> <base encoding>
4190 ::= Tc <this_adjust call-offset> <result_adjust call-offset>
4191 <base encoding> */
4192
4193tree
4194mangle_thunk (tree fn_decl, const int this_adjusting, tree fixed_offset,
4195 tree virtual_offset, tree thunk)
4196{
4197 tree result;
4198
4199 if (abi_version_at_least (11))
4200 maybe_check_abi_tags (fn_decl, thunk, 11);
4201
4202 start_mangling (fn_decl);
4203
4204 write_string ("_Z");
4205 write_char ('T');
4206
4207 if (!this_adjusting)
4208 {
4209 /* Covariant thunk with no this adjustment */
4210 write_char ('c');
4211 mangle_call_offset (integer_zero_node, NULL_TREE);
4212 mangle_call_offset (fixed_offset, virtual_offset);
4213 }
4214 else if (!DECL_THUNK_P (fn_decl))
4215 /* Plain this adjusting thunk. */
4216 mangle_call_offset (fixed_offset, virtual_offset);
4217 else
4218 {
4219 /* This adjusting thunk to covariant thunk. */
4220 write_char ('c');
4221 mangle_call_offset (fixed_offset, virtual_offset);
4222 fixed_offset = ssize_int (THUNK_FIXED_OFFSET (fn_decl));
4223 virtual_offset = THUNK_VIRTUAL_OFFSET (fn_decl);
4224 if (virtual_offset)
4225 virtual_offset = BINFO_VPTR_FIELD (virtual_offset);
4226 mangle_call_offset (fixed_offset, virtual_offset);
4227 fn_decl = THUNK_TARGET (fn_decl);
4228 }
4229
4230 /* Scoped name. */
4231 write_encoding (fn_decl);
4232
4233 result = finish_mangling_get_identifier ();
4234 if (DEBUG_MANGLE)
4235 fprintf (stderr, "mangle_thunk = %s\n\n", IDENTIFIER_POINTER (result));
4236 return result;
4237}
4238
4239struct conv_type_hasher : ggc_ptr_hash<tree_node>
4240{
4241 static hashval_t hash (tree);
4242 static bool equal (tree, tree);
4243};
4244
4245/* This hash table maps TYPEs to the IDENTIFIER for a conversion
4246 operator to TYPE. The nodes are IDENTIFIERs whose TREE_TYPE is the
4247 TYPE. */
4248
4249static GTY (()) hash_table<conv_type_hasher> *conv_type_names;
4250
4251/* Hash a node (VAL1) in the table. */
4252
4253hashval_t
4254conv_type_hasher::hash (tree val)
4255{
4256 return (hashval_t) TYPE_UID (TREE_TYPE (val));
4257}
4258
4259/* Compare VAL1 (a node in the table) with VAL2 (a TYPE). */
4260
4261bool
4262conv_type_hasher::equal (tree val1, tree val2)
4263{
4264 return TREE_TYPE (val1) == val2;
4265}
4266
4267/* Return an identifier for the mangled unqualified name for a
4268 conversion operator to TYPE. This mangling is not specified by the
4269 ABI spec; it is only used internally. */
4270
4271tree
4272mangle_conv_op_name_for_type (const tree type)
4273{
4274 tree *slot;
4275 tree identifier;
4276
4277 if (type == error_mark_node)
4278 return error_mark_node;
4279
4280 if (conv_type_names == NULL)
4281 conv_type_names = hash_table<conv_type_hasher>::create_ggc (31);
4282
4283 slot = conv_type_names->find_slot_with_hash (type,
4284 (hashval_t) TYPE_UID (type),
4285 INSERT);
4286 identifier = *slot;
4287 if (!identifier)
4288 {
4289 char buffer[64];
4290
4291 /* Create a unique name corresponding to TYPE. */
4292 sprintf (buffer, "operator %lu",
4293 (unsigned long) conv_type_names->elements ());
4294 identifier = get_identifier (buffer);
4295 *slot = identifier;
4296
4297 /* Hang TYPE off the identifier so it can be found easily later
4298 when performing conversions. */
4299 TREE_TYPE (identifier) = type;
4300
4301 /* Set bits on the identifier so we know later it's a conversion. */
4302 IDENTIFIER_OPNAME_P (identifier) = 1;
4303 IDENTIFIER_TYPENAME_P (identifier) = 1;
4304 }
4305
4306 return identifier;
4307}
4308
4309/* Handle ABI backwards compatibility for past bugs where we didn't call
4310 check_abi_tags in places where it's needed: call check_abi_tags and warn if
4311 it makes a difference. If FOR_DECL is non-null, it's the declaration
4312 that we're actually trying to mangle; if it's null, we're mangling the
4313 guard variable for T. */
4314
4315static void
4316maybe_check_abi_tags (tree t, tree for_decl, int ver)
4317{
4318 if (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME_SET_P (t))
4319 return;
4320
4321 tree oldtags = get_abi_tags (t);
4322
4323 mangle_decl (t);
4324
4325 tree newtags = get_abi_tags (t);
4326 if (newtags && newtags != oldtags
4327 && abi_version_crosses (ver))
4328 {
4329 if (for_decl && DECL_THUNK_P (for_decl))
4330 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (t), OPT_Wabi,
4331 "the mangled name of a thunk for %qD changes between "
4332 "-fabi-version=%d and -fabi-version=%d",
4333 t, flag_abi_version, warn_abi_version);
4334 else if (for_decl)
4335 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (for_decl), OPT_Wabi,
4336 "the mangled name of %qD changes between "
4337 "-fabi-version=%d and -fabi-version=%d",
4338 for_decl, flag_abi_version, warn_abi_version);
4339 else
4340 warning_at (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (t), OPT_Wabi,
4341 "the mangled name of the initialization guard variable "
4342 "for %qD changes between -fabi-version=%d and "
4343 "-fabi-version=%d",
4344 t, flag_abi_version, warn_abi_version);
4345 }
4346}

4348/* Write out the appropriate string for this variable when generating
4349 another mangled name based on this one. */
4350
4351static void
4352write_guarded_var_name (const tree variable)
4353{
4354 if (DECL_NAME (variable)
4355 && strncmp (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (variable)), "_ZGR", 4) == 0)
4356 /* The name of a guard variable for a reference temporary should refer
4357 to the reference, not the temporary. */
4358 write_string (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (DECL_NAME (variable)) + 4);
4359 else
4360 write_name (variable, /*ignore_local_scope=*/0);
4361}
4362
4363/* Return an identifier for the name of an initialization guard
4364 variable for indicated VARIABLE. */
4365
4366tree
4367mangle_guard_variable (const tree variable)
4368{
4369 if (abi_version_at_least (10))
4370 maybe_check_abi_tags (variable);
4371 start_mangling (variable);
4372 write_string ("_ZGV");
4373 write_guarded_var_name (variable);
4374 return finish_mangling_get_identifier ();
4375}

4405/* Return true iff FN is a thread_local wrapper function. */
4406
4407bool
4408decl_tls_wrapper_p (const tree fn)
4409{
4410 if (TREE_CODE (fn) != FUNCTION_DECL)
4411 return false;
4412 tree name = DECL_NAME (fn);
4413 return strncmp (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (name), TLS_WRAPPER_PREFIX,
4414 strlen (TLS_WRAPPER_PREFIX)) == 0;
4415}

4417/* Return an identifier for the name of a temporary variable used to
4418 initialize a static reference. This isn't part of the ABI, but we might
4419 as well call them something readable. */
4420
4421static GTY(()) int temp_count;
4422
4423tree
4424mangle_ref_init_variable (const tree variable)
4425{
4426 start_mangling (variable);
4427 write_string ("_ZGR");
4428 check_abi_tags (variable);
4429 write_name (variable, /*ignore_local_scope=*/0);
4430 /* Avoid name clashes with aggregate initialization of multiple
4431 references at once. */
4432 write_unsigned_number (temp_count++);
4433 return finish_mangling_get_identifier ();
4434}

4436/* Given a CLASS_TYPE, such as a record for std::bad_exception this
4437 function generates a mangled name for the vtable map variable of
4438 the class type. For example, if the class type is
4439 "std::bad_exception", the mangled name for the class is
4440 "St13bad_exception". This function would generate the name
4441 "_ZN4_VTVISt13bad_exceptionE12__vtable_mapE", which unmangles as:
4442 "_VTV<std::bad_exception>::__vtable_map". */
4443
4444
4445char *
4446get_mangled_vtable_map_var_name (tree class_type)
4447{
4448 char *var_name = NULL;
4449 const char *prefix = "_ZN4_VTVI";
4450 const char *postfix = "E12__vtable_mapE";
4451
4452 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (class_type) == RECORD_TYPE);
4453
4454 tree class_id = DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (TYPE_NAME (class_type));
4455
4456 if (strstr (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (class_id), "<anon>") != NULL)
4457 {
4458 class_id = get_mangled_id (TYPE_NAME (class_type));
4459 vtbl_register_mangled_name (TYPE_NAME (class_type), class_id);
4460 }
4461
4462 unsigned int len = strlen (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (class_id)) +
4463 strlen (prefix) +
4464 strlen (postfix) + 1;
4465
4466 var_name = (char *) xmalloc (len);
4467
4468 sprintf (var_name, "%s%s%s", prefix, IDENTIFIER_POINTER (class_id), postfix);
4469
4470 return var_name;
4471}
